contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:33.559 --> 00:37.494
[♪♪♪]

00:47.473 --> 00:49.107
[DOOR BELL JINGLES]

01:05.458 --> 01:08.226
LOVELY.
VERY NICE.

01:08.327 --> 01:09.393
PERFECT.

01:09.495 --> 01:10.995
OKAY, JUST BE CAREFUL
LOADING IT IN THE VAN.

01:11.097 --> 01:12.029
THANK YOU.

01:13.432 --> 01:16.901
BETTY, THE CENTERPIECES
ARE PERFECT, JUST BEAUTIFUL.

01:17.003 --> 01:17.935
AND THE BOUQUET?

01:18.037 --> 01:19.670
ALREADY AT THE
CHURCH WITH EMILY.

01:19.773 --> 01:22.073
OF COURSE IT IS.
SHE'S A GOOD GIRL.

01:23.676 --> 01:24.642
OH, YES!
COME ON OUT.

01:24.744 --> 01:25.609
PUT THEM IN THE VAN.

01:25.711 --> 01:27.678
THOSE ARE LOVELY.

01:38.491 --> 01:39.556
HEY!

01:39.659 --> 01:43.360
THIS ISN'T A RACE TRACK,
YOU KNOW!

01:43.462 --> 01:45.496
AND, ROSEANNE,
I'M THINKING,

01:45.598 --> 01:46.898
INSTEAD OF STARTING
WITH THE FIRST DANCE,

01:47.000 --> 01:48.365
WE HAVE THE GROOM
SAY A FEW WORDS.

01:48.467 --> 01:49.566
I'M REALLY THINK
IT'LL BE LOVELY.

01:49.669 --> 01:51.368
IT'S OBVIOUS THIS COUPLE
IS MEANT FOR EACH ANOTHER...

01:51.470 --> 01:52.870
YEAH, UH,
PUT A PIN ON THAT.

01:52.972 --> 01:54.772
UM, WE MIGHT HAVE
A LITTLE PROBLEM.

01:54.874 --> 01:55.673
OKAY, SEE THESE?

01:55.775 --> 01:56.908
THEY DON'T MATCH.

01:57.010 --> 01:58.943
THESE FLOWERS ARE WHITER
THAN MY DRESS.

01:59.045 --> 02:00.077
OKAY, NO,
IT'S NO PROBLEM.

02:00.180 --> 02:01.946
UM, EMILY,
SWEETHEART?

02:02.048 --> 02:03.681
IT APPEARS THAT THE
FLOWERS ARE CLASHING

02:03.783 --> 02:04.682
WITH THE BRIDE'S DRESS.

02:04.784 --> 02:05.983
CAN YOU FIX IT?

02:06.085 --> 02:07.618
NOT A PROBLEM.
VANESSA, COME WITH ME.

02:07.720 --> 02:08.619
LOOK AT THAT EMILY.

02:08.721 --> 02:11.021
SO TOGETHER, SO
GROUNDED, SO PERFECT.

02:11.124 --> 02:12.423
I STILL CAN'T
FIGURE OUT

02:12.525 --> 02:13.757
WHY SHE AND COLLIN
NEVER WORKED OUT.

02:13.860 --> 02:15.726
OKAY, NOW IS NOT THE TIME
TO DISCUSS YOUR SON'S LOVE LIFE,

02:15.829 --> 02:17.328
OKAY?

02:17.430 --> 02:20.331
ESPECIALLY WHEN THE GROOM
SEEMS TO BE MISSING.

02:20.433 --> 02:23.567
I'M ON IT.

02:23.669 --> 02:25.870
YOU KNOW, THAT DRESS REALLY
MAKES THE GREEN IN YOUR EYES,

02:25.972 --> 02:27.004
LIKE, POP.

02:27.106 --> 02:28.105
[GIGGLES]

02:31.077 --> 02:33.311
OH, THERE YOU ARE.

02:33.412 --> 02:35.012
DO YOU WANNA GET MARRIED?

02:41.420 --> 02:42.586
[PASTOR]: DO YOU, ROBERT GRANT,

02:42.688 --> 02:46.057
TAKE VANESSA FRASER TO BE
YOUR LAWFULLY WEDDED WIFE?

02:46.159 --> 02:47.624
I DO.

02:49.229 --> 02:51.362
AND DO YOU, VANESSA FRASER,

02:51.464 --> 02:55.032
TAKE ROBERT GRANT TO BE
YOUR LAWFULLY WEDDED HUSBAND?

02:55.134 --> 02:57.668
I DO.

02:57.770 --> 02:59.337
ROBERT AND VANESSA...

02:59.438 --> 03:01.305
SEE? PERFECT.

03:01.407 --> 03:03.107
[PASTOR] MARRIAGE OFFERS YOU
THE PROMISE OF LOVE,

03:03.209 --> 03:05.276
WHICH IS TRUE
AND MATURE.

03:05.378 --> 03:06.410
I NOW PRONOUNCE YOU...

03:06.512 --> 03:09.380
HUSBAND AND WIFE.

03:09.482 --> 03:10.714
YOU MAY KISS THE BRIDE.

03:12.551 --> 03:14.385
[APPLAUSE]

03:20.093 --> 03:23.460
[♪♪♪]

03:23.562 --> 03:24.461
AW!

03:24.563 --> 03:26.097
OKAY, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT!

03:26.199 --> 03:27.131
JUST ONE FOR ME
BEFORE YOU GO.

03:37.710 --> 03:39.110
[FRIENDS]: BYE!

03:44.884 --> 03:47.251
I NEED YOU TO TAKE
A LOOK AT SOMETHING.

03:56.996 --> 03:59.530
I HEARD HE WAS MOVING
NEXT TO OUR SHOP.

04:05.038 --> 04:05.937
[MARCO SPEAKS ITALIAN]

04:06.039 --> 04:08.005
ON THE RIGHT SIDE,
A LITTLE HIGHER.

04:08.107 --> 04:09.073
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON.

04:09.175 --> 04:10.007
THEY DIDN'T SEND A NOTE
ABOUT IT OR ANYTHING.

04:10.109 --> 04:11.842
JUST BRING IT UP.

04:11.945 --> 04:13.244
IT'S A LITTLE TOO LOW
ON THE RIGHT-HAND SIDE.

04:13.346 --> 04:15.012
MAKE IT... YEAH.

04:15.114 --> 04:16.547
YES, PERFECT, LIKE THAT.

04:16.649 --> 04:17.714
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

04:17.817 --> 04:19.951
OKAY, EXCUSE ME?
EXCUSE ME!

04:20.053 --> 04:23.254
YOU JUST PLACED YOUR SIGN
IN FRONT OF OUR WEDDING CHAPEL.

04:23.356 --> 04:24.355
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING?

04:24.457 --> 04:25.423
OH, YOU LIKE THAT?

04:25.524 --> 04:26.790
PERSONALLY,

04:26.892 --> 04:28.826
I THINK THEY WENT A LITTLE
TOO HEAVY ON THE AIRBRUSHING.

04:28.928 --> 04:30.527
I'M MARCO, MARCO AMORINI.

04:31.530 --> 04:33.097
ROSEANNE.
YOUR NEW NEIGHBOR.

04:33.199 --> 04:35.299
FROM THE WEDDING PLACE
NEXT DOOR!

04:35.401 --> 04:36.400
WELL, IT'S A PLEASURE
TO FINALLY MEET YOU.

04:37.570 --> 04:39.103
WELL, THAT'S MY LITTLE
WEDDING PLACE NEXT DOOR....

04:39.205 --> 04:40.771
WEDDING PLANNING,
TO BE EXACT.

04:40.873 --> 04:41.672
NOW, WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO
ABOUT YOUR SIGNAGE?

04:41.774 --> 04:43.140
I'M SO SORRY.

04:43.242 --> 04:44.775
I'VE GOT A 12:00
ANY MINUTE.

04:44.877 --> 04:45.609
<i>CIAO, BELLE</i>!

04:48.448 --> 04:49.713
UNBELIEVABLE.

04:49.815 --> 04:50.881
YOU'RE TELLING ME.

04:53.853 --> 04:55.052
WHOO...

04:55.154 --> 04:56.653
WELL, I'M OFF TO MAKE DINNER

04:56.755 --> 04:59.556
AND TO HELP GARY NEGOTIATE
OUR CURFEW FOR OUR DAUGHTER.

04:59.658 --> 05:01.625
WELL, THANK YOU FOR
EVERYTHING, ROSEANNE.

05:01.727 --> 05:03.995
I COULD NOT HAVE PULLED
IT OFF WITHOUT YOU.

05:04.097 --> 05:06.830
WE CANNOT HAVE A DIVORCE
ATTORNEY NEXT DOOR!

05:06.932 --> 05:09.500
WELL, YOU FIGURE OUT A WAY
TO GET RID OF CAPTAIN GORGEOUS,

05:09.602 --> 05:10.534
AND I'M GOING HOME.

05:10.636 --> 05:11.535
NIGHT-NIGHT.

05:11.637 --> 05:12.603
GOOD NIGHT.

05:17.710 --> 05:18.542
OH, I GOT THAT FOR YA.

05:18.644 --> 05:21.379
THANK YOU.

05:21.481 --> 05:23.481
YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK
WE WERE FORMALLY INTRODUCED.

05:23.582 --> 05:24.982
I'M MARCO AMORINI.

05:25.084 --> 05:26.884
AH, WENDY.
WENDY HAMPTON.

05:26.986 --> 05:28.319
WELL, NICE TO MEET
YOU, WENDY HAMPTON.

05:29.322 --> 05:30.287
GOOD NIGHT.

05:52.745 --> 05:53.710
WELL, DENNIS...

05:53.812 --> 05:55.913
LOOKS LIKE WE PULLED OFF
ANOTHER ONE TODAY.

05:57.650 --> 05:59.483
EXCEPT FOR MY NEW NEIGHBOR.

06:02.388 --> 06:05.489
[FRIENDLY KNOCKING]

06:12.265 --> 06:14.165
LOGAN!

06:14.267 --> 06:16.100
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

06:16.202 --> 06:17.501
DATE NIGHT, REMEMBER?

06:18.837 --> 06:20.871
OH...
RIGHT, YEAH, OF COURSE.

06:20.973 --> 06:22.639
I'M SO SORRY.

06:22.741 --> 06:24.075
YOU WILL NOT BELIEVE
THE DAY I HAD.

06:24.177 --> 06:27.611
A DIVORCE ATTORNEY HAS MOVED IN
RIGHT NEXT DOOR TO MY SHOP!

06:27.713 --> 06:29.713
OH...

06:29.815 --> 06:31.382
WELL, IT IS MOVIE NIGHT,
BUT IF YOU'D RATHER,

06:31.484 --> 06:32.516
WE COULD STAY IN
AND PLAY "WORDORAMA".

06:32.618 --> 06:34.385
OH, RIGHT, YEAH.

06:34.487 --> 06:37.154
WOW, I HAVEN'T PLAYED
WORDORAMA IN YEARS.

06:37.256 --> 06:38.655
GOTTA WARN YA,
I'M PRETTY GOOD.

06:40.093 --> 06:42.025
OKAY, THEN.

06:43.563 --> 06:45.362
OKAY...
MITOCHONDRIA.

06:45.465 --> 06:47.798
THAT IS A TRIPLE-WORD SCORE,
AND THAT IS...

06:47.900 --> 06:48.832
60 POINTS FOR ME.

06:48.934 --> 06:50.501
MITOCHONDRIA?

06:50.603 --> 06:54.572
IT'S A MEMBRANE-BOUND ORGANELLE
FOUND IN MOST EUKARYOTIC CELLS.

06:56.875 --> 06:57.674
YOUR TURN.

06:57.776 --> 06:58.742
OKAY!

06:58.844 --> 07:01.011
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S SEE.

07:02.482 --> 07:03.481
[BLOWS AIR OUT
IN RASPBERRY]

07:05.151 --> 07:06.117
UH, THE TIMER IS...

07:06.219 --> 07:07.918
MYEH!

07:08.020 --> 07:09.553
[PHONE RINGS]

07:09.655 --> 07:11.222
[SIGHS]
DOESN'T COUNT.

07:11.324 --> 07:12.456
HELLO?

07:12.558 --> 07:13.924
[COLLIN]:
<i>HEY, MOM.</i>

07:14.026 --> 07:15.926
COLLIN! SWEETHEART, I WAS
JUST THINKING ABOUT YOU.

07:16.028 --> 07:17.428
<i>I JUST WANTED</i>
<i>TO LET YOU KNOW</i>

07:17.530 --> 07:18.962
<i>THAT I'M COMING HOME</i>
<i>TOMORROW MORNING.</i>

07:19.064 --> 07:20.397
YOU ARE?
TOMORROW MORNING?

07:20.500 --> 07:21.798
IT'S THE MIDDLE
OF THE SEMESTER.

07:21.900 --> 07:22.833
IS-- IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

07:22.935 --> 07:23.934
<i>YEAH, I'LL EXPLAIN</i>
<i>WHEN I SEE YOU.</i>

07:24.036 --> 07:25.869
<i>I LOVE YOU.</i>

07:25.971 --> 07:28.272
OKAY... OKAY,
I LOVE YOU, TOO, BABY.

07:29.542 --> 07:30.774
THAT WAS COLLIN.

07:30.876 --> 07:31.742
HE'S COMING HOME
TOMORROW MORNING.

07:31.844 --> 07:33.076
HMM.

07:33.179 --> 07:34.512
UH, SHOULD I RESET THE TIMER?

07:35.881 --> 07:37.381
[DOORBELL RINGS]

07:37.483 --> 07:38.749
YOU KNOW WHAT?

07:38.851 --> 07:41.418
WOULD IT BE OKAY
IF WE JUST, UH...

07:41.521 --> 07:42.453
FINISH THIS NEXT WEEK?

07:42.555 --> 07:45.122
I PROMISE,
I WON'T TOUCH A THING.

07:45.224 --> 07:47.024
OKAY, I'LL JUST MAKE NOTES.

07:49.495 --> 07:50.361
DAD!

07:50.463 --> 07:52.829
HEY, KID, CAN I COME IN?

07:52.931 --> 07:55.032
IT'S COLD OUT THERE.

07:55.134 --> 07:56.033
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

07:56.135 --> 07:57.334
COLLIN CALLED ME
THIS MORNING...

07:57.436 --> 07:58.602
SAID HE WAS COMING HOME.

07:58.704 --> 08:00.103
HE ASKED ME TO BE HERE.

08:00.206 --> 08:01.738
OH, I DIDN'T MEAN
TO INTERRUPT YOUR DATE.

08:01.840 --> 08:03.940
COLLIN CALLED YOU THIS MORNING?

08:04.043 --> 08:05.342
WONDER WHY HE DIDN'T
CALL ME EARLIER.

08:05.444 --> 08:07.010
EVENING, RAY.

08:07.112 --> 08:08.212
LOGAN, GOOD TO SEE YOU.

08:08.314 --> 08:10.914
DAD, DID COLLIN TELL YOU
WHY HE WAS COMING HOME?

08:11.016 --> 08:12.716
HE HAS SOME NEWS.

08:12.818 --> 08:14.084
OH, HEY, THEN
WE CAN FINISH OUR GAME.

08:14.187 --> 08:15.852
UH, NO, I'M SORRY, LOGAN.

08:15.954 --> 08:17.588
I'VE GOT TO GET
TO THE STORE.

08:17.690 --> 08:19.256
I HAVE NOTHING TO FIX COLLIN
FOR BREAKFAST,

08:19.358 --> 08:21.225
AND I KNOW HE'LL BE HUNGRY.

08:22.761 --> 08:23.860
[DOOR CLOSES]

08:23.962 --> 08:25.563
DO YOU LOVE WORDORAMA?

08:25.665 --> 08:26.564
COME ON!

08:26.666 --> 08:27.998
SURE.

08:41.145 --> 08:42.379
AH, ALMOST.

08:42.481 --> 08:43.880
[RAY]: WELL, I MISS YOU,
TOO, MY SUGAR BEAR,

08:43.982 --> 08:46.116
BUT I PROMISE I'LL
MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

08:46.219 --> 08:47.818
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

08:47.920 --> 08:49.253
BYE.

08:50.223 --> 08:51.054
SO WHAT'S HER NAME?

08:52.157 --> 08:53.023
DIXIE ROSE...

08:53.125 --> 08:53.924
AND ONE FINE LADY,
I MIGHT ADD.

08:54.026 --> 08:55.959
AREN'T THEY ALL?

08:57.029 --> 08:57.994
HONEY, IT'S ALL
PART OF THE JOURNEY.

08:59.865 --> 09:00.864
[CAR HORN HONKS OUTSIDE]

09:00.966 --> 09:02.399
HE'S HERE!

09:04.637 --> 09:05.769
MOM?

09:05.871 --> 09:07.904
COLLIN!
OH, SWEETIE!

09:08.006 --> 09:09.607
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

09:09.709 --> 09:10.507
ARE YOU OKAY?

09:10.610 --> 09:12.243
YEAH, I'M FINE.

09:12.345 --> 09:14.211
OH! UH, AND...
WHO'S THIS?

09:14.313 --> 09:17.381
MOM, GRANDPA...
THIS IS SOPHIA.

09:17.483 --> 09:18.782
NICE TO MEET YOU, SOPHIA.

09:18.884 --> 09:19.883
AND YOU.

09:19.985 --> 09:21.118
SO...

09:21.220 --> 09:23.754
I GUESS THIS IS THE SURPRISE.
[LAUGHS]

09:26.992 --> 09:28.325
OH, WELL...
COME ON IN.

09:28.427 --> 09:29.393
I MADE BREAKFAST.

09:29.495 --> 09:31.528
COLLIN, ALL YOUR FAVORITES.

09:31.631 --> 09:32.996
SOPHIA, PLEASE JOIN US.

09:40.273 --> 09:41.171
SOPHIA...

09:41.274 --> 09:42.939
YOU CAN SIT
RIGHT HERE...

09:43.041 --> 09:44.107
ACTUALLY, MOM...

09:44.209 --> 09:45.309
I'M SORRY, I NEVER GOT
A CHANCE TO TELL YOU,

09:45.411 --> 09:46.443
BUT I DON'T EAT MEAT.

09:46.545 --> 09:47.645
I'M VEGAN.

09:47.747 --> 09:49.513
YOU'RE WHAT?

09:49.615 --> 09:51.114
WE'RE VEGAN.

09:51.216 --> 09:52.549
WHAT'S THAT?
SOME KIND OF RELIGION?

09:53.619 --> 09:54.618
NO, WE JUST BELIEVE

09:54.720 --> 09:56.287
THAT IT'S HEALTHIER
AND MORE HUMANE.

09:56.389 --> 09:58.422
WE DON'T EAT ANIMALS
OR ANIMAL PRODUCTS.

09:58.524 --> 10:01.158
AS SOPHIA SAYS, NOTHING TASTES
AS GOOD AS BEING VEGAN FEELS.

10:01.260 --> 10:02.993
[LAUGHS]
RIGHT.

10:03.095 --> 10:04.328
WE GOTTA GO.

10:04.430 --> 10:06.797
WE HAVE SOME BUSINESS IN TOWN
THAT WE GOTTA TAKE CARE OF.

10:06.899 --> 10:07.931
I WAS HOPING
THAT WE COULD DO

10:08.033 --> 10:09.099
FAMILY DINNER
HERE TONIGHT, THOUGH.

10:09.201 --> 10:13.036
WELL, OF COURSE,
BUT... I'M CONFUSED.

10:13.138 --> 10:14.271
I'LL EXPLAIN IT ALL
TO YOU TONIGHT.

10:14.373 --> 10:15.839
IS IT OKAY
IF SOPHIA'S FATHER JOINS US?

10:15.941 --> 10:18.141
SURE.

10:18.243 --> 10:19.810
'KAY, BYE.
LOVE YOU.

10:19.912 --> 10:22.346
IT'S GREAT TO FINALLY MEET YOU,
MRS. HAMPTON.

10:22.448 --> 10:23.580
COLLIN HAS TOLD ME
SO MUCH ABOUT YOU.

10:23.683 --> 10:24.615
SEE YOU BOTH TONIGHT!

10:24.717 --> 10:25.849
SEE YOU TONIGHT.

10:30.222 --> 10:31.622
[ROSEANNE]:
DINNER WITH HER FATHER?

10:31.724 --> 10:33.691
THAT SOUNDS SERIOUS.

10:33.793 --> 10:34.658
I DON'T KNOW.

10:34.760 --> 10:36.327
THIS IS
ALL SO SUDDEN.

10:36.429 --> 10:37.994
AND COLLIN NEVER SHOWED
ANY INTEREST

10:38.096 --> 10:40.831
IN THIS "HEALTHIER,
MORE HUMANE" STUFF,

10:40.933 --> 10:42.333
AND NOW HE'S VEGAN?

10:42.435 --> 10:43.500
WHAT IS THAT ABOUT?

10:43.602 --> 10:45.202
I DON'T KNOW,
BUT I'M NOT BUYING IT.

10:45.304 --> 10:47.003
[LAUGHS]

10:47.105 --> 10:48.004
OOH...

10:48.106 --> 10:50.441
I KNOW HE'S THE MORTAL ENEMY,
I KNOW,

10:50.543 --> 10:55.078
BUT WHOO!
HE IS GORGEOUS.

10:55.180 --> 10:57.080
AND YOU ARE
HAPPILY MARRIED.

10:57.182 --> 11:00.116
MM-HMM,
BUT NO HARM IN DREAMING.

11:01.687 --> 11:04.455
I JUST DON'T KNOW WHY COLLIN
WOULDN'T HAVE SIMPLY CALLED ME

11:04.557 --> 11:06.223
AND TOLD ME ABOUT
A NEW GIRLFRIEND

11:06.325 --> 11:10.828
RATHER THAN JUST SHOW UP
WITH THIS... THIS SOPHIA...

11:10.929 --> 11:12.229
AND WHAT DO WE KNOW
ABOUT THIS SOPHIA?

11:12.331 --> 11:14.130
NOTHING.
THAT'S THE POINT.

11:14.233 --> 11:16.767
[WOMAN]: IF HE WANTS A FIGHT,
I'LL GIVE HIM A FIGHT!

11:16.869 --> 11:18.569
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU-- YOU WILL GIVE HIM A FIGHT.

11:18.671 --> 11:21.037
HEY, THE McDOUGALS,
THEY BOOKED THEIR APPOINTMENT.

11:21.139 --> 11:22.005
WHO?

11:22.107 --> 11:23.774
THE McDOUGALS!

11:23.876 --> 11:25.609
WHAT IS GOING ON OVER THERE?

11:25.711 --> 11:29.780
[CLIENT]: YOU KNOW HOW
HARD I HAVE TO WORK?

11:29.882 --> 11:30.647
THEY CAN'T BE YELLING
LIKE THAT.

11:30.750 --> 11:33.016
I CAN'T EVEN HEAR MYSELF THINK!

11:33.118 --> 11:35.486
MAYBE THIS DIVORCE
ISN'T SO AMICABLE?

11:35.588 --> 11:37.187
I WORKED AND WORKED AND WORKED!

11:37.289 --> 11:38.321
ALL OF THE THINGS I DID
FOR HIM,

11:38.424 --> 11:40.290
AND ALL THE STUPID PARTIES
I THREW FOR HIM...

11:40.393 --> 11:41.958
COULD THIS DAY
GET ANY WORSE?

11:42.060 --> 11:44.928
[CLIENT, SCREAMING]:
IT'S NOT FINE! IT'S NOT FINE!

11:57.969 --> 11:59.468
[DOORBELL RINGS]

12:04.075 --> 12:04.908
HEY, BABY.

12:05.010 --> 12:06.442
HI!

12:06.544 --> 12:07.911
WHERE'S YOUR DAD?

12:08.013 --> 12:09.012
HE'S COMING
RIGHT BEHIND ME.

12:09.114 --> 12:11.681
HI, MRS. HAMPTON.
THIS IS FOR YOU.

12:11.783 --> 12:13.482
IT'S JUST A LITTLE DESSERT
I MADE.

12:15.653 --> 12:17.053
[COLLIN]: YOUR VEGAN
PROFITEROLES!

12:17.155 --> 12:18.754
THAT'S MY FAVORITE.

12:18.857 --> 12:22.558
OH, WELL, THANK YOU,
BUT IT WASN'T REALLY NECESSARY.

12:22.660 --> 12:24.360
EXCUSE ME,
JUST A CALL WITH A CLIENT.

12:26.298 --> 12:27.763
DAD, THIS IS MY
BOYFRIEND, COLLIN.

12:27.866 --> 12:28.597
NICE TO MEET YOU.

12:28.700 --> 12:30.166
THIS IS HIS GRANDFATHER, RAY.

12:30.268 --> 12:31.067
RAY.

12:31.169 --> 12:32.135
AND HIS MOTHER, WENDY.

12:33.371 --> 12:35.972
UH, RIGHT... I...

12:36.074 --> 12:37.406
THINK WE'VE...
ALREADY MET.

12:37.508 --> 12:38.474
WE HAVE?

12:40.278 --> 12:41.110
UH, HOPE YOU LIKE RED.

12:41.213 --> 12:43.947
YOU'RE SOPHIA'S FATHER?

12:45.851 --> 12:46.883
[QUIETLY] IT
JUST GOT WORSE.

12:46.985 --> 12:48.184
[BRIGHTLY] DAD, WILL
YOU SHOW THEM INSIDE?

12:48.286 --> 12:49.819
[RAY]: FOLLOW ME.

12:51.522 --> 12:53.223
LET ME GET
THE DOOR FOR YOU.

13:00.131 --> 13:02.098
COLLIN, LET ME SPEAK TO YOU.

13:02.200 --> 13:04.367
LOOK, I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
WHY AREN'T YOU IN SCHOOL?

13:04.469 --> 13:06.535
AND WHAT IS WITH THIS SOPHIA
AND HER DAD?

13:06.637 --> 13:08.338
MOM, TRUST ME,
IT'S ALL GOING TO BE OKAY.

13:09.040 --> 13:09.939
[MARCO]: SOPHIA.

13:10.041 --> 13:12.275
THANKS, DAD.

13:15.013 --> 13:16.179
-THANK YOU.
-OH!

13:16.281 --> 13:17.580
OKAY.

13:18.917 --> 13:20.016
TA-DAH!

13:21.386 --> 13:23.219
VEAL PARMIGIANA!

13:23.321 --> 13:25.454
COLLIN, YOUR FAVORITE!

13:25.556 --> 13:26.622
WONDERFUL!
YOU COOK ITALIAN?

13:26.724 --> 13:27.623
I TRY.

13:28.894 --> 13:30.659
MOM, I ALREADY TOLD YOU...

13:30.762 --> 13:32.028
WE'RE VEGANS.
REMEMBER?

13:32.130 --> 13:33.796
OH, DON'T BE SILLY.

13:33.899 --> 13:35.631
THIS HAS ALWAYS BEEN
YOUR FAVORITE.

13:36.701 --> 13:37.666
NO, REALLY, MOM.

13:37.769 --> 13:38.868
SOPHIA AND I,
WE CAN'T EAT THIS.

13:38.970 --> 13:40.870
IT'S NOT WHAT
WE BELIEVE IN.

13:40.972 --> 13:43.373
BUT THE SALAD
LOOKS DELICIOUS.

13:43.474 --> 13:44.774
ARE THOSE
HEIRLOOM TOMATOES?

13:44.876 --> 13:46.409
SOPHIA, DARLING,
WE'RE GUESTS.

13:46.511 --> 13:48.711
JUST PLEASE EAT
WHATEVER'S SERVED.

13:48.813 --> 13:50.146
PLUS, A LITTLE MEAT
IS HEALTHY FOR YOU.

13:50.248 --> 13:52.681
ACTUALLY, DAD,
IT'S MUCH HEALTHIER THIS WAY.

13:52.784 --> 13:54.683
AND I FEEL GREAT.

13:54.786 --> 13:55.985
IN FACT, I'VE NEVER BEEN BETTER.

13:57.222 --> 13:59.889
WELL, WENDY'S VEAL PARMIGIANA'S
ALWAYS BEEN MY FAVORITE.

13:59.991 --> 14:01.057
[COLLIN LAUGHS]

14:04.195 --> 14:05.261
SO, MOM,

14:05.363 --> 14:06.595
HOW DO YOU AND MR. AMORINI
KNOW EACH ANOTHER?

14:06.697 --> 14:10.499
WELL, APPARENTLY, MR. AMORINI
IS MY NEW NEIGHBOR AT WORK.

14:11.602 --> 14:13.202
[RAY]: OH YEAH?

14:13.305 --> 14:14.237
WHAT KIND OF BUSINESS
DO YOU RUN?

14:14.339 --> 14:16.472
UH...

14:16.574 --> 14:17.340
I'M A DIVORCE ATTORNEY.

14:17.442 --> 14:18.607
[LAUGHS]
REALLY?

14:18.709 --> 14:20.776
WHAT A HOOT!

14:20.878 --> 14:22.445
A DIVORCE ATTORNEY
AND A WEDDING PLANNER,

14:22.547 --> 14:23.947
SIDE BY SIDE.

14:24.049 --> 14:25.448
ONE-STOP SHOPPING.

14:27.385 --> 14:28.952
OR THE UNIVERSE
WORKING AGAINST ME.

14:29.054 --> 14:30.420
OR MAYBE YOU COULD LOOK AT IT

14:30.521 --> 14:32.355
AS THE UNIVERSE OPENING UP
FOR YOU.

14:33.724 --> 14:35.358
MAYBE WE COULD OPEN UP THE WINE?

14:35.460 --> 14:36.459
YES.

14:37.462 --> 14:38.227
ALLOW ME.

14:38.330 --> 14:39.963
OH, NO, I'VE GOT IT.

14:42.300 --> 14:43.599
SO...

14:43.701 --> 14:46.135
SOPHIA AND I, WE HAVE
SOME EXCITING NEWS.

14:46.237 --> 14:47.837
[SOPHIA]: GO AHEAD,
SWEETHEART.

14:47.939 --> 14:49.538
YOU TELL THEM.

14:49.640 --> 14:51.640
SOPHIA AND I...

14:51.742 --> 14:52.608
WE'RE GETTING MARRIED!

14:52.710 --> 14:54.410
[COUGHS]

14:54.512 --> 14:56.179
[SOPHIA]:
AND THERE'S MORE.

14:56.281 --> 14:58.114
WE'RE GOING TO BE
ORGANIC FARMERS.

14:59.417 --> 15:00.483
ISN'T IT GREAT?

15:03.554 --> 15:04.454
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

15:04.555 --> 15:05.754
DAD, DON'T START.

15:05.857 --> 15:07.290
YOU ARE 22 YEARS OLD.

15:07.392 --> 15:09.058
YOU ARE TOO YOUNG
TO GET MARRIED.

15:09.160 --> 15:10.026
WHAT, YOU EXPECT ME
TO SIT HERE

15:10.128 --> 15:11.394
AND JUST BE HAPPY

15:11.496 --> 15:12.395
THAT YOU'RE DROPPING OUT
OF LAW SCHOOL?

15:12.497 --> 15:13.929
COLLIN, YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS!

15:14.032 --> 15:16.332
AND WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"ORGANIC FARMING?"

15:16.434 --> 15:20.136
DOES THIS HAVE SOMETHING TO DO
WITH THAT VEGAN THING?

15:20.238 --> 15:21.104
NO, MOM.

15:21.206 --> 15:22.538
SOPHIA AND I
HAVE BEEN PLANNING THIS

15:22.640 --> 15:23.639
FOR A WHILE.

15:24.742 --> 15:26.142
HOW LONG HAVE YOU EVEN
KNOWN EACH OTHER?

15:27.278 --> 15:28.277
TWO MONTHS.

15:31.616 --> 15:32.715
WELL...

15:32.817 --> 15:35.284
SOPHIA...

15:35.387 --> 15:37.987
IT APPEARS THAT THIS BOY
HAS MADE YOU LOSE YOUR SENSES.

15:38.089 --> 15:39.788
HOLD ON A SECOND.

15:39.891 --> 15:41.857
THIS BOY DIDN'T HAVE
ANY OF THESE CRAZY IDEAS

15:41.959 --> 15:44.127
UNTIL HE MET YOUR GIRL.

15:44.229 --> 15:46.362
MOM, I KNOW
THAT THIS IS A LOT TO PROCESS,

15:46.464 --> 15:47.497
BUT WE KNOW WHAT WE'RE DOING.

15:47.598 --> 15:49.332
MY DAUGHTER'S NOT GOING
TO BECOME A FARMER.

15:49.434 --> 15:51.501
I RAISED YOU
TO BE MY LAW PARTNER.

15:51.602 --> 15:53.036
THIS IS SO TYPICAL
OF YOU, DAD.

15:53.138 --> 15:53.903
MR. AMORINI, PLEASE.

15:54.005 --> 15:55.271
I'M NOT TALKING TO YOU.

15:55.373 --> 15:56.772
WE HAVE THOUGHT THIS THROUGH.

15:56.874 --> 15:57.673
YOU ARE DESTROYING
MY DAUGHTER'S FUTURE.

15:57.775 --> 15:58.674
[WENDY]: EXCUSE ME!

15:58.776 --> 16:00.143
HE WAS JUST FINE

16:00.245 --> 16:02.011
AND ON TRACK
FOR A GREAT LAW CAREER.

16:02.113 --> 16:03.446
AND I'M QUITE CERTAIN

16:03.548 --> 16:06.282
THIS WHOLE FARMING IDEA
WASN'T EVEN HIS!

16:06.384 --> 16:08.151
OH, REALLY?

16:08.253 --> 16:10.953
AND YOU THINK THAT SOPHIA
WOULD GIVE UP HER DREAM

16:11.056 --> 16:12.255
OF PARTNERING UP WITH ME
AT THE FIRM

16:12.357 --> 16:13.389
TO, WHAT, MILK COWS?

16:13.491 --> 16:14.557
THAT'S RIDICULOUS!

16:14.659 --> 16:15.925
UNLESS YOUR SON
TALKED HER INTO IT.

16:17.062 --> 16:18.294
THIS MIGHT BE A GOOD
TIME TO LEAVE.

16:18.396 --> 16:20.963
MY SON WAS EATING MEAT
BEFORE HE MET YOUR DAUGHTER.

16:21.066 --> 16:22.498
MEAT?
WHO CARES ABOUT MEAT?

16:22.600 --> 16:24.867
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT HER CAREER!
MY BUSINESS!

16:24.969 --> 16:27.002
OH, OF COURSE,
YOUR BUSINESS.

16:27.105 --> 16:30.039
AND WHAT KIND OF PERSON
OPENS A DIVORCE OFFICE

16:30.141 --> 16:31.474
RIGHT NEXT TO A WEDDING PLANNER?

16:31.576 --> 16:33.543
YOU'RE SELLING FAIRY TALES.

16:35.413 --> 16:36.579
MARRIAGE IS NOT A FAIRY TALE.

16:49.327 --> 16:50.726
THIS HAS BEEN
AN ENLIGHTENING EVENING.

16:52.330 --> 16:54.663
<i>CIAO.</i>

16:58.903 --> 16:59.969
CAN I HAVE SOME WINE?

17:00.071 --> 17:02.004
[GROANS]

17:16.721 --> 17:18.154
MORNING!
I SAVED YOU SOME MUFFINS.

17:18.256 --> 17:19.188
GOOD MORNING.

17:19.290 --> 17:20.623
COLLIN,
ABOUT LAST NIGHT...

17:20.724 --> 17:22.592
IT'S OKAY, MOM.
I UNDERSTAND.

17:22.693 --> 17:23.492
YOU DO?

17:23.595 --> 17:25.228
OH, THANK GOODNESS,

17:25.329 --> 17:26.596
BECAUSE YOU CAN SEE
WHY DROPPING OUT OF SCHOOL

17:26.696 --> 17:28.063
AND RUSHING INTO
THIS MARRIAGE

17:28.165 --> 17:29.198
IS A BAD IDEA.

17:29.300 --> 17:30.699
I MEAN, IT'S OBVIOUS

17:30.801 --> 17:31.634
YOU'RE HEAD OVER HEELS
FOR SOPHIA...

17:31.736 --> 17:33.469
MOM, WHAT ARE YOU
SO AFRAID OF?

17:33.571 --> 17:36.705
COLLIN, YOU'RE SO YOUNG.
YOU'RE 22.

17:36.807 --> 17:38.641
YOU AND DAD WERE 21
WHEN YOU HAD ME.

17:38.743 --> 17:40.075
THAT WAS DIFFERENT.

17:40.178 --> 17:42.578
AND I NEVER WANTED YOU TO REPEAT
WHAT YOUR FATHER AND I DID.

17:42.680 --> 17:44.079
YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO FINISH COLLEGE.

17:44.182 --> 17:46.215
BESIDES, YOUR FATHER AND I
HAD A SOLID PLAN, WE...

17:46.317 --> 17:47.216
SO DO WE.

17:47.318 --> 17:49.252
MOM, I GOTTA GO.

17:49.354 --> 17:51.987
I HAVE A MEETING AT THE BANK.
THANK YOU FOR THE MUFFINS.

17:53.358 --> 17:54.423
THE BANK?

17:54.526 --> 17:56.125
WHAT ARE YOU DOING AT THE BANK?

17:59.464 --> 18:02.565
[SIGHS]
HEAVEN HELP ME.

18:18.849 --> 18:19.848
[SINISTER MUSIC]

18:32.830 --> 18:33.962
JOSH, COME ON.

18:34.065 --> 18:36.299
YOU KNOW AS WELL AS I DO
THAT IF MY CLIENT WANTED TO,

18:36.401 --> 18:38.100
SHE COULD GO AFTER
ALL YOUR CLIENT'S ASSETS.

18:38.203 --> 18:39.635
EVEN THE ONES
STASHED OVERSEAS.

18:39.737 --> 18:43.539
EXCUSE ME, YOUR CAR IS
IN MY PARKING SPOT.

18:45.910 --> 18:46.842
JUST ADVISE YOUR CLIENT...

18:46.944 --> 18:49.745
ADVISE YOUR CLIENT
TO PLAY FAIR,

18:49.847 --> 18:50.979
AND SO WILL WE.

18:51.082 --> 18:54.950
IT'S THE LEAST HE CAN DO
AFTER 10 YEARS OF MARRIAGE.

18:55.052 --> 18:57.853
ALL RIGHT.

18:57.955 --> 18:59.655
I'LL SEE YOU THERE.

18:59.757 --> 19:00.756
I WILL.

19:02.059 --> 19:02.925
[CAR REMOTE BEEPS]

19:03.027 --> 19:06.095
[CAR ALARM BLARES]

19:06.197 --> 19:07.230
[TURNS IT OFF]

19:07.332 --> 19:09.732
WHO DOES HE THINK I AM?
SOME KIND OF VALET?

19:21.846 --> 19:23.646
[LOUD SCRAPING SOUND]

19:26.618 --> 19:28.150
NO, NO, NO, NO!

19:28.253 --> 19:30.819
OH MY G... WHAT'D YOU DO?
HOW DID YOU...

19:30.921 --> 19:32.221
YOUR FAMILY IS A DISASTER!

19:32.323 --> 19:33.522
LIKEWISE.

19:33.625 --> 19:35.891
WHAT... WHAT IS
WRONG WITH YOU?

19:35.993 --> 19:37.360
WHY DID YOU EVEN NEED
TO MOVE MY CAR?

19:37.462 --> 19:38.294
THERE ARE PLENTY
OF SPOTS.

19:38.396 --> 19:39.962
DO YOU NOT SEE THE SIGN?

19:40.064 --> 19:42.064
"PERFECT WEDDINGS
BY HAMPTON?"

19:42.166 --> 19:43.165
I'VE BEEN PARKING
IN THIS SPOT

19:43.268 --> 19:45.368
SINCE MY HUSBAND AND I
OPENED THIS BUSINESS.

19:45.470 --> 19:48.337
RIGHT.

19:48.439 --> 19:50.139
YOUR HUSBAND.

19:50.241 --> 19:52.341
SOPHIA TOLD ME
HE PASSED AWAY.

19:52.443 --> 19:54.543
I'M SORRY.
LOOK, JUST...

19:54.646 --> 19:56.312
FORGET ABOUT THE SCRATCH.
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

19:56.414 --> 19:57.647
I'M JUST GONNA PARK
IN THE STREET

19:57.749 --> 19:59.948
UNTIL WE CAN GET THIS WHOLE
PARKING THING FIGURED OUT.

20:00.050 --> 20:01.317
IT'LL BE SAFER THAT WAY.

20:01.419 --> 20:02.851
THANK YOU.

20:10.027 --> 20:11.260
YOU SCRATCHED HIS CAR?

20:11.362 --> 20:13.028
OH, THAT'S RICH.

20:13.130 --> 20:14.830
I DIDN'T MEAN TO.

20:14.932 --> 20:16.399
HIS DAUGHTER
IS BRAINWASHING MY SON.

20:16.501 --> 20:18.434
MAYBE HE IS NOT BRAINWASHED.

20:18.536 --> 20:20.469
MAYBE HE'S IN LOVE.

20:21.972 --> 20:23.806
YOU KNOW...

20:23.908 --> 20:24.873
I SEEM TO RECALL

20:24.975 --> 20:27.242
A YOUNG COUPLE
THAT WAS SO IN LOVE,

20:27.345 --> 20:29.878
THEY ACTUALLY STARTED
THEIR OWN WEDDING BUSINESS.

20:29.980 --> 20:32.481
DENNIS AND I WERE DIFFERENT.

20:32.583 --> 20:34.983
WE WERE HIGH SCHOOL SWEETHEARTS
WHO GREW UP TOGETHER.

20:35.085 --> 20:37.453
COLLIN HAS JUST
MET SOPHIA.

20:37.555 --> 20:38.954
A YEAR AGO,
HE WAS IN LOVE WITH EMILY.

20:39.056 --> 20:40.790
AND NOW, OVERNIGHT,

20:40.891 --> 20:42.591
HE IS DROPPING OUT
OF LAW SCHOOL,

20:42.694 --> 20:44.427
BECOME A VEGAN,
IS GETTING MARRIED,

20:44.529 --> 20:47.196
AND STARTING HIS OWN
ORGANIC FARMING BUSINESS.

20:47.298 --> 20:48.331
[LAUGHS]

20:48.433 --> 20:50.165
YOU DON'T THINK
THAT'S CRAZY?

20:50.267 --> 20:52.067
AH, YOU KNOW,
WE CAN RAISE THEM,

20:52.169 --> 20:54.203
BUT, HOO, WE CANNOT LIVE
THEIR LIVES FOR THEM.

20:54.305 --> 20:55.170
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

20:55.272 --> 20:56.372
TO GET MORE COFFEE.

20:56.474 --> 20:58.341
HEY, McDOUGALS. 10:00.

21:05.556 --> 21:07.422
LARGE COFFEE, DOUBLE SUGAR,
NO CREAM, PLEASE.

21:07.525 --> 21:09.124
SO, WHAT ARE WE
GOING TO DO

21:09.226 --> 21:11.894
ABOUT THIS RIDICULOUS PLAN
OF SOPHIA AND, UM...

21:11.996 --> 21:13.529
UH...

21:13.631 --> 21:14.597
COLLIN?

21:14.699 --> 21:15.965
-MY SON?
-YES.

21:16.066 --> 21:17.299
THE ONE WHO WAS
ON THE RIGHT PATH

21:17.401 --> 21:19.502
BEFORE HE WAS BLINDED
BY THE AMORINI CHARM?

21:20.671 --> 21:21.604
AMORINI CHARM?

21:21.706 --> 21:22.972
[LAUGHS]

21:23.073 --> 21:24.072
HANG ON A SEC,
I GOT THIS.

21:24.174 --> 21:25.207
NO, I GOT IT.

21:25.309 --> 21:26.475
NO, REALLY, I INSIST.

21:26.577 --> 21:27.342
NO, I INSIST.

21:27.444 --> 21:28.744
[CLATTERING]

21:28.846 --> 21:29.645
I GOT IT.

21:29.747 --> 21:30.679
[THWACK]

21:30.781 --> 21:31.780
OW!

21:31.883 --> 21:32.648
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

21:32.750 --> 21:33.582
I'M FINE.

21:33.684 --> 21:34.683
OKAY. I'M SORRY.

21:34.785 --> 21:35.651
[WOMAN]:
YOO-HOO! MARCO!

21:35.753 --> 21:36.485
WHAT?

21:36.587 --> 21:38.554
HI.

21:38.656 --> 21:39.722
BEVERLY!<i> CIAO</i>.

21:39.824 --> 21:40.990
NICE TO SEE YOU.

21:41.091 --> 21:42.491
GOOD TO SEE YOU, TOO.
YEAH, UM...

21:42.593 --> 21:44.660
I WOULD LOVE A MOCHA.

21:44.762 --> 21:46.028
UH, ONE MOCHA,
ONE ESPRESSO.

21:46.130 --> 21:47.029
UH...

21:47.131 --> 21:48.731
[CLATTERS]

21:52.637 --> 21:54.770
UH... I GOT THIS.
HANG ON, I GOT THIS.

21:58.075 --> 21:59.675
[WENDY]: OUR WEDDING
PACKAGE INCLUDES

21:59.777 --> 22:01.276
THE CEREMONY AND
THE RECEPTION,

22:01.378 --> 22:03.412
BOTH OF WHICH
ROSEANNE AND I WILL PLAN DOWN

22:03.514 --> 22:04.847
TO EVERY LAST DETAIL.

22:04.949 --> 22:06.114
FLOWERS, FOOD, CAKE...

22:06.216 --> 22:08.584
NOW, WE HAVE DOWN
THE MAID OF HONOR,

22:08.686 --> 22:10.553
BUT WHO WILL BE
THE BEST MAN?

22:10.655 --> 22:12.287
THAT WILL BE
MY BROTHER, STAN.

22:12.389 --> 22:14.489
UNFORTUNATELY.

22:14.592 --> 22:15.824
[SEAN]: HONEY,
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH THIS.

22:15.927 --> 22:17.092
YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
THAT MEANS TO ME.

22:17.194 --> 22:18.293
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

22:18.395 --> 22:20.362
NO, JUST...

22:20.464 --> 22:21.864
EVERYTHING ABOUT HIM
IS BAD LUCK.

22:21.966 --> 22:23.398
[DOOR OPENS]

22:23.500 --> 22:24.266
HEY, SORRY.

22:24.368 --> 22:25.868
YOU LEFT THIS BEHIND.

22:25.970 --> 22:27.135
SEAN?

22:27.237 --> 22:28.971
SEAN McDOUGAL?

22:29.073 --> 22:32.240
CONGRATULATIONS!
TAKING THE PLUNGE AGAIN, HUH?

22:32.342 --> 22:34.309
WOW!

22:34.411 --> 22:35.878
THAT LAST ONE SURE PUT UP
QUITE A FIGHT, DIDN'T SHE?

22:35.980 --> 22:37.012
BUT I'M SURE THIS TIME,
YOU'LL GET A PRENUP.

22:37.114 --> 22:38.180
THAT IS MY SPECIALITY.

22:38.282 --> 22:39.481
[LAUGHS]

22:39.584 --> 22:42.150
WAIT A MINUTE, WAIT...
YOU WERE MARRIED BEFORE?

22:42.252 --> 22:45.420
WELL, I, I... WANTED TO TALK
TO YOU ABOUT THAT, YEAH.

22:45.522 --> 22:48.123
[WOMAN]: OH, YOU WANTED
TO TALK TO ME ABOUT THAT?

22:48.225 --> 22:49.892
I'M SO, SO SORRY.

22:49.994 --> 22:51.894
WILL YOU EXCUSE US?

22:51.996 --> 22:53.028
YOU KNOW WHAT? I THINK
I MIGHT HAVE TO GO.

22:53.130 --> 22:54.863
WAIT, WAIT,
PLEASE, WAIT...

22:54.966 --> 22:57.566
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

22:57.668 --> 22:59.434
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING?

22:59.536 --> 23:01.303
I'M IN THERE TRYING
TO PLAN A COUPLE'S WEDDING,

23:01.405 --> 23:03.706
AND YOU'RE BRINGING UP
HIS DIVORCE AND PRENUPS?

23:03.808 --> 23:05.841
I'M JUST TRYING
TO PROTECT HIM.

23:05.943 --> 23:07.175
YOU GIVE A MARRIAGE
TWO WEEKS,

23:07.277 --> 23:08.477
AND I WILL GIVE YOU
GROUNDS FOR DIVORCE,

23:08.579 --> 23:10.212
AND BY THE SOUNDS OF IT,
THEY DON'T EVEN NEED TWO WEEKS.

23:10.314 --> 23:12.247
WHEN DID YOU BECOME SO CYNICAL?

23:12.349 --> 23:13.916
MOST MARRIAGES END

23:14.018 --> 23:15.550
WITH BOTH PEOPLE
TRYING TO INFLICT

23:15.653 --> 23:17.987
AS MUCH PAIN ON ONE ANOTHER
AS HUMANLY POSSIBLE,

23:18.089 --> 23:19.187
WHICH IS EXACTLY WHY

23:19.289 --> 23:20.689
SOPHIA WILL NEVER MARRY
YOUR SON,

23:20.791 --> 23:21.824
NOT IF I CAN HELP IT.

23:21.926 --> 23:23.959
GREAT, AT LEAST
WE AGREE ON ONE THING.

23:24.061 --> 23:24.860
GREAT.

23:24.962 --> 23:26.128
SO WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
ABOUT IT?

23:26.230 --> 23:28.230
ME?
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO ABOUT IT?

23:28.332 --> 23:30.666
WELL, I'VE ALWAYS
BEEN ABLE TO TALK TO COLLIN.

23:30.768 --> 23:32.001
REALLY?

23:32.103 --> 23:33.468
[LAUGHS]

23:33.570 --> 23:34.937
OH, NO, NO,
I COULD TELL BY THE WAY

23:35.039 --> 23:36.404
HE SHARED HIS ENGAGEMENT
WITH YOU.

23:38.308 --> 23:39.808
I WILL HANDLE MY SON.

23:39.910 --> 23:41.610
YOU HANDLE SOPHIA
HOWEVER YOU WISH.

23:41.712 --> 23:42.577
FINE.

23:42.680 --> 23:45.147
FINE.

23:45.249 --> 23:46.248
OH, DON'T, NO!

23:46.350 --> 23:48.350
COME ON, I WAS INSIDE
FOR TWO SECONDS!

23:48.452 --> 23:50.218
WHERE DID YOU
COME FROM, ANYWAY?

23:50.320 --> 23:51.286
I HAD TO MAKE CHANGE!

23:51.388 --> 23:53.188
LOOK... AGH...

24:01.365 --> 24:02.597
WONDERFUL MEAL.

24:02.700 --> 24:03.666
IS THERE DESSERT?

24:03.768 --> 24:05.000
YES.

24:05.102 --> 24:06.168
COLLIN, WILL YOU HELP ME CLEAR?

24:09.140 --> 24:11.273
SO, RAY, UM...

24:11.375 --> 24:13.142
YOU'RE A HUNTER?

24:13.243 --> 24:15.177
OH, YEAH. YOU?

24:15.279 --> 24:16.679
NO, NO, NO.

24:16.781 --> 24:17.980
YOU SHOULD TRY IT!

24:19.449 --> 24:20.549
MAYBE!

24:20.651 --> 24:23.018
THANKS FOR DINNER, MOM,
BUT I HAVE TO GO.

24:23.120 --> 24:24.319
OH, WAIT, NO...

24:24.421 --> 24:25.587
BEFORE YOU GO,
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

24:25.690 --> 24:27.990
YOUR TRIP TO THE BANK
THIS MORNING,

24:28.092 --> 24:30.225
DID IT HAVE SOMETHING TO DO WITH
THIS WHOLE FARMING BUSINESS?

24:30.327 --> 24:32.360
YEAH, WE'RE APPLYING
FOR A SMALL BUSINESS LOAN,

24:32.462 --> 24:34.496
BUT IT'S KINDA COMPLICATED.

24:34.598 --> 24:36.264
I MIGHT NEED TO CASH IN
ON MY EDUCATION FUND.

24:36.366 --> 24:38.167
COLLIN!

24:38.268 --> 24:40.235
OKAY, WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"CASH IN" YOUR EDUCATION FUND?

24:40.337 --> 24:42.637
MOM, I HAVE IT HANDLED.

24:42.740 --> 24:44.439
OKAY, BUT THIS IS ALL
MOVING SO QUICKLY,

24:44.541 --> 24:45.941
AND YOU'RE COMMITTING SO MUCH,

24:46.043 --> 24:47.409
I'M AFRAID YOU'RE GETTING IN
OVER YOUR HEAD.

24:47.511 --> 24:49.044
MOM, DIDN'T YOU AND DAD
USED TO TELL ME

24:49.146 --> 24:51.113
TO GO FOR MY DREAMS?

24:51.215 --> 24:52.514
THIS IS ME GOING FOR IT.

24:52.616 --> 24:55.617
OKAY, BUT WHAT ABOUT YOUR DREAM
OF BECOMING A LAWYER?

24:57.487 --> 24:59.955
I THINK THAT WAS MORE
YOUR DREAM, NOT MINE.

25:01.358 --> 25:02.958
OKAY,
BUT THIS IS JUST SO DRASTIC,

25:03.060 --> 25:04.593
AND I THINK
YOU'RE BEING IMPULSIVE.

25:04.695 --> 25:07.096
MOM, I LOVE YOU,

25:07.198 --> 25:08.764
BUT THIS IS MY LIFE.

25:08.866 --> 25:10.065
I HAVE TO GO.

25:12.269 --> 25:13.869
OF COURSE YOU DO.

25:17.474 --> 25:18.607
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

25:18.709 --> 25:20.075
HE NEVER BEHAVED
LIKE THIS WITH EMILY.

25:20.177 --> 25:22.878
I MEAN,
THEY WERE SO GROUNDED.

25:22.980 --> 25:25.214
THEY MADE SENSE--
LIKE YOU AND I, LOGAN.

25:25.315 --> 25:27.750
QUESTION, IS THIS LACTOSE FREE?

25:27.852 --> 25:29.484
I DON'T TOLERATE DAIRY
THAT WELL.

25:29.586 --> 25:31.120
GIVE THE KID A BREAK.

25:31.222 --> 25:32.554
HE'S HAVING FUN.

25:32.656 --> 25:34.589
WHAT, LIKE YOU, DAD?

25:34.691 --> 25:36.625
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT FOR HIM?

25:36.727 --> 25:39.128
A WHOLE STRING OF GIRLFRIENDS
AND FAILED RELATIONSHIPS?

25:39.230 --> 25:40.996
EASY NOW.
I'M STILL YOUR FATHER.

25:41.098 --> 25:43.165
AND I'M STILL COLLIN'S MOTHER.

25:43.267 --> 25:44.800
YOU KNOW, STATISTICS INDICATE

25:44.902 --> 25:46.701
MOST KIDS DON'T LISTEN
TO THEIR PARENTS.

25:46.804 --> 25:47.803
NOW, THAT'S A PROVEN FACT.

25:51.608 --> 25:52.507
YOU'RE RIGHT!

25:52.609 --> 25:54.943
YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY RIGHT.

25:55.045 --> 25:57.813
WE NEED A HIGHER POWER.

25:58.715 --> 25:59.848
WHERE YOU GOING?

25:59.950 --> 26:01.449
TO CALL A HIGHER POWER.

26:01.551 --> 26:03.718
[SPEED DIALS]

26:03.821 --> 26:06.054
PASTOR MACY?
IT'S WENDY.

26:11.061 --> 26:11.660
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

26:11.762 --> 26:12.995
I GOT SOMETHING FOR YOU.

26:14.198 --> 26:15.798
READY?

26:17.301 --> 26:18.801
HUH? WHAT DO
YOU THINK?

26:18.903 --> 26:20.502
DAD, I ALREADY TOLD YOU.

26:20.604 --> 26:22.504
I'M NOT GOING INTO PRACTICE
WITH YOU.

26:22.606 --> 26:24.773
COLLIN AND I
ARE GOING TO BE

26:24.875 --> 26:26.374
ORGANIC FARMERS.

26:26.476 --> 26:29.744
[MUTTERS IN ITALIAN]

26:29.847 --> 26:31.713
DARLING...

26:31.816 --> 26:34.449
YOU AND I BOTH KNOW HOW
DIFFICULT MARRIAGE CAN BE.

26:34.551 --> 26:36.651
AFTER YOUR MOTHER LEFT,
IT BROKE OUR HEARTS.

26:36.753 --> 26:37.953
I JUST DON'T WANT TO SEE YOU
GO THROUGH THAT AGAIN.

26:38.055 --> 26:40.088
DAD, THAT WAS YOUR MARRIAGE.

26:40.191 --> 26:41.556
IT'S DIFFERENT
WITH COLLIN AND ME.

26:41.658 --> 26:43.158
THAT'S WHAT THEY ALL SAY.

26:43.260 --> 26:44.359
BUT TRUST ME, THINGS CHANGE.

26:44.461 --> 26:45.393
I MEAN, FOR GOODNESS SAKE,

26:45.495 --> 26:47.296
DIVORCE PAID
FOR YOUR LAW SCHOOL,

26:47.397 --> 26:48.297
NOT MARRIAGE.

26:48.398 --> 26:50.065
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

26:51.035 --> 26:52.500
[WENDY]: SORRY!

26:52.602 --> 26:53.802
I DON'T MEAN
TO INTERRUPT, BUT...

26:53.904 --> 26:56.671
I WONDER IF YOU AND COLLIN
MIGHT DO SOMETHING FOR ME.

26:56.773 --> 26:59.374
MEET WITH MY PRE-MARITAL
COUNSELOR, PASTOR MACY.

26:59.476 --> 27:00.775
MOM...

27:00.878 --> 27:02.978
NO, HONEY, IT'S FINE.
WE'D LOVE TO, MRS. HAMPTON.

27:03.080 --> 27:04.546
OH, THAT'S GREAT...

27:04.648 --> 27:07.415
BECAUSE I ALREADY CALLED,
AND HE CAN SEE YOU RIGHT NOW.

27:08.986 --> 27:11.019
PASTOR MACY CAN HELP THEM
"EXAMINE" THEIR CHOICES.

27:13.057 --> 27:14.156
RIGHT.

27:14.258 --> 27:16.091
WELL,
PASTOR MACY'S A GREAT GUY...

27:16.193 --> 27:18.526
SO I THINK WE CAN DO THAT.
LET'S GO.

27:22.166 --> 27:23.899
I TAKE IT YOUR TALK
DIDN'T WORK SO WELL?

27:24.001 --> 27:24.933
PASTOR MACY IS TOUGH.

27:25.035 --> 27:27.669
DON'T WORRY. HE'LL
SET THEM STRAIGHT.

27:32.343 --> 27:33.708
[PASTOR]: THE QUESTIONS
I'M ABOUT TO ASK YOU

27:33.810 --> 27:36.011
ARE DIFFICULT.

27:36.113 --> 27:37.846
THEY NEED TO BE DIFFICULT.

27:37.948 --> 27:39.581
BUT DON'T BE AFRAID OF THEM.

27:39.683 --> 27:42.184
MARRIAGE SHOULD NOT BE
ENTERED INTO LIGHTLY.

27:42.286 --> 27:44.286
THERE ARE MANY THINGS
TO CONSIDER.

27:47.992 --> 27:50.492
YOU REALLY THINK
THIS IS GONNA WORK?

27:50.594 --> 27:53.661
IT'S GOT TO.

27:54.865 --> 27:55.898
YOU KNOW,
I WOULD HAVE NEVER THOUGHT

27:56.000 --> 27:58.200
SOPHIA WOULD HAVE DONE
SOMETHING LIKE THIS,

27:58.302 --> 28:00.535
ESPECIALLY AFTER HER MOTHER
LEFT US THE WAY SHE DID.

28:00.637 --> 28:02.604
I'M SORRY.
I HADN'T REALIZED.

28:02.706 --> 28:04.373
HOW OLD WAS SOPHIA?

28:05.642 --> 28:06.975
SHE WAS FIVE.

28:07.077 --> 28:09.677
OH... THAT'S HEARTBREAKING.

28:11.081 --> 28:12.747
HOW OLD WAS COLLIN
WHEN HIS FATHER DIED?

28:12.849 --> 28:14.816
EIGHT.

28:14.919 --> 28:17.219
IT'S HARD FOR A BOY TO GROW UP
WITHOUT A FATHER.

28:17.321 --> 28:20.389
NOT ANY HARDER THAN FOR A GIRL
TO GROW UP WITHOUT HER MOTHER.

28:21.625 --> 28:24.960
YOU KNOW, SOPHIA'S MOM
WILL NEVER BE

28:25.062 --> 28:26.628
WHO SOPHIA WANTS
HER TO BE.

28:26.730 --> 28:28.730
I DON'T KNOW HOW MANY MORE TIMES
SHE'S GOTTA BE LET DOWN

28:28.832 --> 28:30.032
BEFORE SHE REALIZES IT.

28:30.134 --> 28:31.900
WHAT ABOUT COLLIN?

28:32.002 --> 28:33.435
WAS HE CLOSE
WITH HIS FATHER?

28:33.537 --> 28:35.670
OH, VERY.

28:35.772 --> 28:37.272
THEY DID EVERYTHING TOGETHER.

28:37.374 --> 28:38.706
CAMPING, BIKING...

28:38.809 --> 28:41.376
THEY WENT FISHING
ALMOST EVERY WEEKEND.

28:41.478 --> 28:42.744
[DOOR OPENS]

28:44.114 --> 28:46.248
BE PREPARED.
THERE MAY BE TEARS.

28:47.418 --> 28:48.516
[PASTOR]: WENDY!

28:48.618 --> 28:51.486
I HAVE TO SAY,
I'M SURPRISED.

28:51.588 --> 28:53.855
YOUTH CAN, INDEED,
BE PROBLEMATIC

28:53.958 --> 28:56.058
WHEN MAKING SUCH
SERIOUS LIFE DECISIONS,

28:56.160 --> 28:57.592
AND I ALWAYS
RECOMMEND

28:57.694 --> 29:00.062
THAT YOUNG COUPLES
TAKE THEIR TIME,

29:00.164 --> 29:01.763
SPREAD THEIR WINGS.

29:01.865 --> 29:03.031
BUT I CAN CLEARLY SEE

29:03.133 --> 29:04.632
THAT THESE TWO
HAVE THEIR FEET ON THE GROUND

29:04.734 --> 29:06.768
AND A GOOD HEAD
ON THEIR SHOULDERS,

29:06.870 --> 29:08.036
AND I HAVE NO DOUBT

29:08.138 --> 29:10.172
THAT THEY ARE ENTERING
INTO THIS MARRIAGE

29:10.274 --> 29:12.941
WITH LOVE AND REASON.

29:13.043 --> 29:13.908
CONGRATULATIONS, COLLIN.

29:14.011 --> 29:14.843
THANK YOU.

29:14.945 --> 29:16.144
-SOPHIA.
-THANK YOU, PASTOR.

29:27.219 --> 29:28.218
I KNEW THAT
WOULDN'T WORK.

29:28.320 --> 29:29.586
OH, DID YOU?

29:29.689 --> 29:31.288
WELL, IF YOU WERE SO SURE,
WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY SOMETHING?

29:31.390 --> 29:32.422
AT LEAST I'M TRYING.

29:32.524 --> 29:33.691
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
OTHER THAN POINTING OUT

29:33.793 --> 29:35.092
WHAT I'M DOING WRONG?

29:35.194 --> 29:36.259
AT LEAST I'LL THINK
OF A BETTER PLAN

29:36.361 --> 29:37.260
THEN MARRIAGE COUNSELING.

29:37.362 --> 29:38.829
FINE, THEN DO IT.

29:38.931 --> 29:40.530
FINE, I WILL.

29:40.632 --> 29:42.733
WELL, AS FUTURE IN-LAWS,

29:42.835 --> 29:45.202
YOU GUYS ARE GETTING ALONG
JUST GREAT.

29:52.745 --> 29:53.844
[DOORBELL RINGS]

29:56.782 --> 29:58.515
-MARCO!
-HI.

29:58.617 --> 29:59.382
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

29:59.484 --> 30:01.151
MR. AMORINI!

30:01.253 --> 30:02.019
YOU READY TO GO?

30:02.121 --> 30:03.020
YOU BET.

30:03.122 --> 30:04.387
WE'RE GOING FISHING.

30:04.489 --> 30:05.622
THAT'S RIGHT...

30:05.725 --> 30:08.092
A LITTLE FATHER-IN-LAW,
SON-IN-LAW BONDING,

30:08.194 --> 30:09.126
JUST THE TWO OF US,

30:09.228 --> 30:10.460
SO WE CAN GET TO KNOW
EACH OTHER BETTER.

30:10.562 --> 30:11.461
SEE YOU IN THE CAR.

30:11.563 --> 30:12.596
EXCUSE ME...

30:12.698 --> 30:14.364
HOW IS FISHING BONDING
GOING TO HELP?

30:15.935 --> 30:17.067
I GOT THIS, ALL RIGHT?

30:17.169 --> 30:19.603
PERSUASION
IS MY SPECIALTY.

30:22.674 --> 30:24.507
WHERE'D YOU GO?
THERE YOU ARE.

30:31.951 --> 30:33.150
HERE, USE...

30:33.252 --> 30:35.619
YEAH, USE ONE OF THESE.
IT'S EASIER.

30:35.669 --> 30:37.806
[MARCO]: SO, COLLIN... IT'S A PITY
THAT, WITH ALL THE...

30:37.856 --> 30:40.804
RESPONSIBILITIES OF RUNNING A FARM,
YOU WON'T BE ABLE TO SPEND

30:40.854 --> 30:42.183
MORE FREE DAYS FISHING.

30:42.200 --> 30:43.465
IT'S A LOT TO TAKE ON AT 22.

30:43.567 --> 30:45.168
SOPHIA AND I BOTH THINK

30:45.270 --> 30:50.406
THAT LIVING LIFE TO THE FULLEST
MEANS PURSUING YOUR GOALS.

30:53.311 --> 30:54.677
WELL...

30:54.779 --> 30:57.513
SOPHIA CERTAINLY HAS GROWN UP,

30:57.615 --> 30:59.448
BUT SHE'LL ALWAYS BE
MY LITTLE GIRL.

30:59.550 --> 31:03.252
I MEAN, YOU'VE ONLY BEEN
TOGETHER FOR TWO MONTHS.

31:03.354 --> 31:04.887
MARRIAGE IS FOREVER.

31:05.023 --> 31:06.289
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE READY

31:06.390 --> 31:07.857
TO DEDICATE
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE

31:07.959 --> 31:09.058
TO MY SOPHIA?

31:09.160 --> 31:10.693
YOU'RE BOTH SO YOUNG.

31:10.795 --> 31:14.430
AND IN MY LINE OF WORK,
I CAN TELL YOU...

31:16.000 --> 31:18.000
WHAT YOU'RE FEELING TODAY
WILL PROBABLY VANISH

31:18.102 --> 31:19.335
AT THE FIRST SIGN OF PROBLEMS.

31:19.437 --> 31:22.305
MR. AMORINI...

31:22.406 --> 31:24.573
I KNOW YOU THINK
I'M TOO YOUNG

31:24.675 --> 31:27.509
AND THAT WE'RE LIVING
IN THIS WORLD OF DREAMS,

31:27.611 --> 31:30.813
BUT I DO KNOW THAT MARRIAGE
IS A LIFETIME COMMITMENT,

31:30.915 --> 31:34.616
AND WHEN THINGS AREN'T EASY,
YOU JUST DON'T QUIT.

31:34.719 --> 31:36.618
MAYBE THAT'S WHAT
YOUR CLIENTS DON'T GET.

31:38.089 --> 31:41.357
SIR...

31:41.459 --> 31:43.826
I LOVE YOUR DAUGHTER.

31:43.928 --> 31:45.761
SHE INSPIRES ME
TO BE THE BEST MAN

31:45.864 --> 31:47.196
THAT I CAN POSSIBLY BE.

31:48.833 --> 31:52.068
I KNOW, WITH HER AT MY SIDE,
THAT I CAN ACHIEVE ANYTHING.

31:54.538 --> 31:55.938
I WON'T STAND FOR HER
BEING HURT.

31:56.040 --> 31:58.341
NEITHER WILL I.

32:03.647 --> 32:06.148
HOW DO YOU CAST
THIS DARN THING?

32:06.251 --> 32:07.183
OH, HERE.

32:07.285 --> 32:08.684
NO...

32:08.786 --> 32:09.818
WELL, UH, HERE...

32:09.921 --> 32:10.786
SEE?

32:10.889 --> 32:12.955
OOF!

32:17.495 --> 32:18.694
I'M OKAY.

32:22.700 --> 32:24.333
YEAH, PURPLE'S
MUCH BETTER.

32:24.435 --> 32:25.634
YEAH.

32:25.736 --> 32:26.802
[DOOR OPENS]

32:31.709 --> 32:33.809
[LAUGHS]

32:35.213 --> 32:37.780
OKAY, SO...
DID YOU CATCH ANY FISH?

32:37.882 --> 32:38.915
FUNNY.

32:39.017 --> 32:40.049
I KNEW IT.

32:40.151 --> 32:40.849
OH, REALLY?

32:40.952 --> 32:41.650
YEAH, REALLY.

32:41.752 --> 32:43.485
WELL...

32:43.587 --> 32:45.955
I DON'T THINK ANY OF OUR IDEAS
ARE WORKING.

32:46.057 --> 32:46.923
OH, AND COLLIN TOLD ME

32:47.025 --> 32:48.057
THEY'RE GONNA SEE
A FARM TOMORROW.

32:48.159 --> 32:49.225
WHAT?

32:50.494 --> 32:53.062
YOU KNOW, YOU GUYS
COULD THINK OF IT THIS WAY.

32:53.164 --> 32:55.331
THE KIDS SEEM REALLY TENACIOUS.
I MEAN, THINK ABOUT IT.

32:55.433 --> 32:57.300
FARM LIFE?
THAT'S A TOUGH LIFE.

32:58.436 --> 33:00.970
-ARE YOU DONE?
-WE NEED TO GO WITH THEM!

33:01.072 --> 33:03.139
WELL...

33:03.241 --> 33:04.307
ABSOLUTELY.

33:04.409 --> 33:06.575
ON THIS,
I THINK WE CAN AGREE.

33:09.780 --> 33:10.813
HEY, DAD, IT'S ME.

33:10.915 --> 33:12.248
I'M LOOKING FOR COLLIN.
HAVE YOU SEEN HIM?

33:12.350 --> 33:13.715
MARCO JUST GOT BACK
FROM THEIR FISHING TRIP,

33:13.818 --> 33:15.551
AND HE SAID SOMETHING ABOUT
HE AND SOPHIA

33:15.653 --> 33:16.885
GOING TO LOOK FOR A FARM
TOMORROW?

33:16.988 --> 33:17.886
I DON'T KNOW.

33:17.989 --> 33:19.688
A LOT OF GOOD
THIS FISHING TRIP WAS.

33:19.790 --> 33:21.290
THANK YOU.

33:21.392 --> 33:22.891
OH, WAIT, NEVER MIND.
I SEE HIM. OKAY.

33:22.994 --> 33:23.892
HEY, BABY!

33:23.995 --> 33:25.594
HEY!

33:25.696 --> 33:27.096
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR YOU.

33:27.198 --> 33:28.130
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

33:28.232 --> 33:30.066
UH... REFILL.

33:30.168 --> 33:31.667
BUT, UM,
NOW THAT YOU'RE HERE,

33:31.769 --> 33:34.136
HOW WAS YOUR FISHING TRIP
WITH MARCO?

33:34.238 --> 33:35.972
LOOK WHO'S DOING
THE FISHING NOW.

33:36.074 --> 33:37.906
OKAY, SO YOU CAUGHT ME.

33:38.009 --> 33:39.208
SERIOUSLY, HOW'D IT GO?

33:39.310 --> 33:40.042
IT WAS GREAT.

33:40.144 --> 33:41.410
-IT WAS?
-YEAH.

33:41.512 --> 33:43.612
MR. AMORINI'S A GREAT GUY.

33:43.714 --> 33:45.481
HE IS?

33:46.617 --> 33:47.649
I MEAN, YOU KNOW, I MEAN,

33:47.751 --> 33:49.318
OBVIOUSLY,
HE'S NOT A FISHERMAN...

33:49.420 --> 33:50.453
I MEAN, NOT LIKE YOUR DAD.

33:50.554 --> 33:51.820
YEAH. IT'S OKAY.

33:51.922 --> 33:53.689
AND HE GOT BETTER AFTER A WHILE,
AND BESIDES...

33:53.791 --> 33:55.891
I THINK IT'LL BE A GOOD WAY
FOR US TO BOND.

33:55.994 --> 33:57.393
AND I CAN TEACH HIM
HOW TO FISH, AND HE...

33:57.495 --> 33:59.962
SO HE DIDN'T TRY TO TALK YOU
OUT OF YOUR PLAN WITH SOPHIA?

34:00.064 --> 34:02.731
MOM, MR. AMORINI WANTS
WHAT'S BEST FOR HIS DAUGHTER,

34:02.833 --> 34:03.532
AND SO DO I.

34:03.634 --> 34:05.401
AND THAT IS...?

34:05.503 --> 34:07.803
LOOK, MOM, I BETTER GO.

34:07.905 --> 34:09.170
SOPHIA'S WAITING AT THE PARK,

34:09.273 --> 34:10.639
AND I PROMISED I'D MEET
HER WITH SOY LATTES.

34:10.741 --> 34:12.908
OKAY, OKAY. BUT WHAT IS THIS
ABOUT SEEING A FARM?

34:13.011 --> 34:14.710
YEAH,
THERE'S A FARM THAT WE FOUND

34:14.812 --> 34:15.978
THAT WE'RE INTERESTED
IN LEASING.

34:16.080 --> 34:17.413
WELL, YOU KNOW,

34:17.514 --> 34:20.681
I THINK MARCO AND I WOULD LIKE
TO SEE THAT WITH YOU.

34:20.784 --> 34:22.284
YEAH! THAT WOULD BE GREAT!

34:22.387 --> 34:23.284
OKAY!

34:23.388 --> 34:24.286
YOU CAN COME
WITH US.

34:24.389 --> 34:25.286
GREAT!

34:25.389 --> 34:27.023
-YES!
-OKAY! MWAH!

34:52.183 --> 34:52.813
[SPLAT]

34:52.917 --> 34:55.251
OH...

34:56.420 --> 34:57.619
I TOLD HIM TO WEAR BOOTS.

34:57.721 --> 34:59.422
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU AND MUD?

35:01.059 --> 35:02.391
[MAN]: HEY, OVER HERE!

35:02.493 --> 35:03.426
WELCOME!

35:03.528 --> 35:04.393
[COLLIN]: HEY!

35:11.536 --> 35:13.502
OH, THAT'S
A GOOD QUESTION.

35:13.604 --> 35:15.471
ON THE FARM,
WE KEEP LIVESTOCK.

35:18.443 --> 35:20.609
THEY'RE ALL USED
TO BEING HANDLED,

35:20.711 --> 35:21.944
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN

35:22.046 --> 35:23.745
THEY STILL WON'T
GIVE YOU A HARD TIME.

35:23.847 --> 35:24.513
LET ME SHOW YOU
THE BARN.

35:24.615 --> 35:27.349
THAT SOUNDS
LIKE A HANDFUL.

35:27.452 --> 35:29.651
COLLIN, YOU NEVER
EVEN HAD A DOG.

35:29.753 --> 35:31.387
AND REMEMBER WHAT HAPPENED
TO THAT GOLDFISH YOU HAD?

35:31.489 --> 35:32.388
NOT TO WORRY.

35:32.490 --> 35:33.622
YOU'LL GET A FEEL
FOR THE ANIMALS.

35:33.724 --> 35:35.491
OH, BUT YOU TWO
PROBABLY CAME FROM FARMING,

35:35.593 --> 35:36.892
UNLIKE THESE TWO.

35:36.994 --> 35:38.961
ACTUALLY, I WAS
AN ECONOMICS MAJOR,

35:39.063 --> 35:42.531
AND MARIANNE HERE HAS GOT
HER Ph.D. IN PSYCHOLOGY.

35:42.633 --> 35:43.765
COME ON.

35:43.867 --> 35:45.534
I'LL INTRODUCE YOU TO BELLA.

35:49.640 --> 35:51.707
[GOAT BLEATS]

35:55.746 --> 35:56.812
THIS IS BELLA,

35:56.914 --> 35:58.414
OUR NUMBER ONE
MILK PRODUCER.

35:58.516 --> 35:59.982
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO GIVE IT A TRY?

36:01.352 --> 36:02.851
SURE.

36:03.854 --> 36:05.354
[WENDY]: YOU MUST HAVE TO GET UP
AT THE CRACK OF DAWN

36:05.456 --> 36:06.855
TO GET EVERYTHING DONE.

36:06.957 --> 36:07.956
BUT IT'S WORTH IT

36:08.058 --> 36:09.525
WHEN YOU SEE
THE SUNRISE OUT HERE.

36:09.627 --> 36:11.693
YOU'VE NEVER SEEN ANYTHING
MORE BEAUTIFUL.

36:11.795 --> 36:13.195
WELL, MAYBE THE SUNSET.

36:14.165 --> 36:15.063
BE HONEST.

36:15.166 --> 36:16.064
THE PAYOFF
FOR ALL THE HARD WORK...

36:16.167 --> 36:17.065
I MEAN, IT CAN'T BE
THAT MUCH.

36:17.168 --> 36:19.034
WELL, IT WASN'T FOR US,

36:19.137 --> 36:21.137
BUT THE OTHER FARMS
THAT HAVE GONE ORGANIC

36:21.239 --> 36:23.339
AREN'T DOING BAD AT ALL.

36:23.441 --> 36:24.906
WOULD YOU LOOK AT THAT?

36:25.009 --> 36:26.242
HE'S A NATURAL.

36:26.344 --> 36:28.777
[MILK SPATTERS IN BUCKET]

36:28.879 --> 36:30.912
MR. AMORINI?
YOU WANT TO GIVE IT A TRY?

36:31.015 --> 36:32.414
NO... NO, I'M NOT...

36:32.517 --> 36:33.449
OH, COME ON.

36:33.551 --> 36:34.550
I'M NOT GOOD AT...

36:34.652 --> 36:36.619
NO, SHOW SOPHIA THAT
IT'S NOT THAT EASY.

36:44.762 --> 36:46.428
[MILK SPLATTERS IN BUCKET]

36:46.531 --> 36:48.597
I DON'T SEE HOW TURNING
THIS PLACE INTO AN ORGANIC FARM

36:48.699 --> 36:50.266
COULD BE EASY OR CHEAP.

36:50.368 --> 36:51.667
BASED ON MY RESEARCH,

36:51.769 --> 36:52.934
THE LAND NEEDS TO BE
PESTICIDE FREE

36:53.037 --> 36:54.203
FOR AT LEAST 36 MONTHS,

36:54.305 --> 36:56.104
AND YOU NEED
AN ORGANIC SYSTEM PLAN,

36:56.207 --> 36:57.339
YOU HAVE TO BE CERTIFIED...

36:57.441 --> 36:59.308
DAD, WE'VE ALREADY
BEEN IN CONTACT

36:59.410 --> 37:01.710
WITH THE LOCAL CERTIFICATION
AGENCIES.

37:01.812 --> 37:03.111
AND OUR FIELDS HAVE BEEN FALLOW
FOR THE PAST THREE YEARS.

37:03.214 --> 37:05.514
HA HA...

37:05.616 --> 37:07.516
WOW, MR. AMORINI.
YOU'RE A REAL NATURAL AT THAT.

37:08.719 --> 37:09.985
[COW BELLOWS]

37:11.455 --> 37:13.088
[EVERYONE LAUGHS]

37:13.191 --> 37:15.057
[COW MOOS]

37:15.159 --> 37:16.392
[ROOSTER CROWS]

37:20.931 --> 37:23.499
LOOKS LIKE IT'S GOING TO NEED
A LOT OF MAINTENANCE.

37:24.935 --> 37:26.101
COLLIN, LOOK!

37:26.204 --> 37:29.672
THIS IS WHERE WE SHOULD
HAVE THE WEDDING!

37:29.773 --> 37:31.440
YEAH, SOPHIA,
THAT'S BRILLIANT!

37:31.542 --> 37:33.542
THIS IS WHERE WE'RE GONNA
BUILD OUR LIVES.

37:33.644 --> 37:35.844
YEAH, THE SMELL OF COWS,
THAT'S REALLY ROMANTIC.

37:35.946 --> 37:37.313
WHERE WOULD YOU EVEN HAVE
A RECEPTION?

37:37.415 --> 37:39.014
NO, WE'D WANT IT
TO BE CASUAL,

37:39.116 --> 37:42.150
BE MORE ABOUT OUR FRIENDS
BEING PART OF THE CELEBRATION.

37:42.253 --> 37:43.485
LET'S NOT HAVE
A FORMAL RECEPTION.

37:43.588 --> 37:46.855
OKAY, WAIT A MINUTE.
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

37:46.957 --> 37:49.391
[SOPHIA]: WE WANT A SIMPLE
REFLECTION OF OUR LIFESTYLE,

37:49.493 --> 37:50.726
RIGHT DOWN TO THE CAKE.

37:50.828 --> 37:51.893
DEFINITELY VEGAN.

37:51.995 --> 37:52.861
YES.

37:52.963 --> 37:54.096
AGAIN WITH THE VEGAN.

37:54.198 --> 37:55.698
DO THEY EVEN MAKE
A VEGAN CAKE?

37:55.799 --> 37:56.998
CARROT CAKE?

38:02.139 --> 38:03.339
I KNOW.

38:03.441 --> 38:04.573
I DON'T EVEN
RECOGNIZE COLLIN.

38:04.675 --> 38:06.508
IT MAKES ME WONDER
WHAT KIND OF A JOB I DID.

38:06.611 --> 38:09.411
NO MATTER HOW GOOD
OF A FATHER I WAS OR NOT,

38:09.513 --> 38:11.213
I'LL TAKE CARE OF HER NOW.

38:13.183 --> 38:15.251
DAD, ISN'T THIS
PLACE PERFECT?

38:15.353 --> 38:17.553
WELL, I'D HARDLY
CALL IT PERFECT.

38:17.655 --> 38:18.454
JUST LISTEN.

38:18.556 --> 38:19.755
[WIND CHIMES]

38:19.857 --> 38:21.156
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

38:21.259 --> 38:22.358
IT'S LIKE THE WIND CHIMES WE HAD
ON OUR BACK PORCH, REMEMBER?

38:25.329 --> 38:26.027
WHAT'S THIS?

38:26.130 --> 38:27.363
YOUR PRENUP.

38:28.932 --> 38:30.733
ARE YOU SERIOUS?
I DON'T NEED A PRENUP.

38:32.102 --> 38:33.902
THAT'S JUST EVEN MORE FOOLISH
THAN THIS WHOLE FARM BUSINESS.

38:34.004 --> 38:37.306
MR. AMORINI, I APPRECIATE
YOUR CONCERN, BUT...

38:37.408 --> 38:38.440
YOU'RE IMPOSSIBLE.

38:42.980 --> 38:45.281
THAT'S IT?

38:45.383 --> 38:46.915
THAT'S YOU
TAKING CARE OF HER?

38:47.017 --> 38:48.517
WELL, IF SHE INSISTS

38:48.619 --> 38:49.785
ON GOING THROUGH
WITH THIS WHOLE FARMING DEAL,

38:49.887 --> 38:50.919
AT LEAST I WANT HER PROTECTED.

38:51.021 --> 38:54.022
LOOK, I DON'T WANT TO SEE
COLLIN HURT EITHER,

38:54.124 --> 38:55.724
BUT A PRENUP
IS NOT THE SOLUTION.

38:57.194 --> 38:59.395
WELL, WHAT DO YOU
SUGGEST, WENDY?

38:59.497 --> 39:00.462
I DON'T KNOW.

39:02.400 --> 39:04.032
HOW ABOUT THIS?

39:04.134 --> 39:05.501
HOW ABOUT WE STOP FIGHTING
EACH OTHER,

39:05.603 --> 39:09.505
AND WE START
WORKING TOGETHER.

39:09.607 --> 39:10.673
I CAN DO THAT.

39:10.775 --> 39:13.275
[CAR DRIVES AWAY]

39:18.816 --> 39:19.815
LOOKS LIKE I'LL BE
NEEDING A RIDE.

39:21.585 --> 39:23.552
I GOT SOME ROOM IN MY TRUNK.

39:47.364 --> 39:50.399
[COLLIN]: DON'T WORRY,
WE'LL FIND A WAY TO GET IT.

39:52.170 --> 39:54.036
I MEAN, IT WAS JUST PERFECT.

39:54.138 --> 39:56.939
THE HOUSE, THE BARN, YOU...

39:58.843 --> 39:59.675
[LAUGHS]

39:59.777 --> 40:00.943
YEAH.

40:03.347 --> 40:05.280
22 YEARS
I'VE KNOWN THAT BOY,

40:05.382 --> 40:07.116
I'VE NEVER SEEN HIM
SO HAPPY.

40:07.218 --> 40:09.685
[COLLIN]: SOPHIA,
WE WILL MAKE IT WORK.

40:09.787 --> 40:12.454
WE CAN DO
ANYTHING, RIGHT?

40:12.556 --> 40:14.323
'KAY.

40:14.425 --> 40:15.490
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

40:20.131 --> 40:21.797
OKAY, YOU'RE ALL SET.

40:21.899 --> 40:23.565
OH, YOU LOOK AMAZING!

40:23.667 --> 40:24.900
WHY, WHAT'S
THE OCCASION?

40:25.002 --> 40:27.069
NO OCCASION.
JUST COFFEE.

40:27.171 --> 40:28.871
MARCO AND I NEED TO DISCUSS
THE KIDS.

40:28.973 --> 40:30.906
OH, MARCO? MM-HMM.

40:31.008 --> 40:31.941
WELL, THAT'S AN AWFULLY
FANCY DRESS

40:32.043 --> 40:33.609
FOR A LATTE.

40:36.347 --> 40:37.079
LOGAN!

40:37.181 --> 40:38.547
WHAT A SURPRISE!

40:38.649 --> 40:39.749
YEAH, JUST THOUGHT I'D COME BY

40:39.851 --> 40:40.649
AND SEE IF YOU HAD ANY IDEAS
FOR MOVIES TONIGHT.

40:40.752 --> 40:41.617
IT'S MOVIE FRIDAY, REMEMBER?

40:41.719 --> 40:43.919
OF COURSE.

40:44.021 --> 40:45.821
NOPE, I CAN'T THINK OF ANYTHING.

40:45.923 --> 40:49.058
MM, DON'T WORRY, I'LL BRING
A DVD FROM MY PLACE.

40:49.160 --> 40:50.793
SO... OH, THIS IS FOR YOU.

40:50.895 --> 40:53.595
TWO CREAMS, NO SUGAR,
JUST THE WAY YOU LIKE IT.

40:53.697 --> 40:56.098
ACTUALLY, LOGAN,
IT'S NO CREAM, TWO SUGARS.

40:56.200 --> 40:58.333
IT'S NO BIG DEAL, REALLY.

40:58.435 --> 40:59.668
IT'S THE THOUGHT THAT COUNTS.

41:00.671 --> 41:02.404
WELL, ALL RIGHT.

41:02.506 --> 41:03.272
UH...

41:03.374 --> 41:04.473
WELL, SEE YOU TONIGHT.

41:04.575 --> 41:06.308
OKAY! I'LL
SEE YOU TONIGHT.

41:21.959 --> 41:23.025
SO, IF YOU'LL AGREE,

41:23.127 --> 41:25.060
WE'LL GO AHEAD AND FILE
THE ANNULMENT REQUEST.

41:25.163 --> 41:26.195
[KNOCKS GENTLY]

41:26.297 --> 41:27.396
GREAT.

41:34.738 --> 41:36.471
WELL, I LOOK FORWARD
TO WORKING WITH YOU.

41:45.316 --> 41:47.049
SHALL WE?

41:56.260 --> 41:58.127
LARGE COFFEE, DOUBLE SUGAR,
NO CREAM.

42:00.031 --> 42:02.031
RIGHT. THANK YOU.

42:04.068 --> 42:05.634
THAT WOMAN
IN YOUR OFFICE EARLIER...

42:05.736 --> 42:07.236
OH, RIGHT, YES. UM....

42:07.338 --> 42:10.239
WELL, IT TURNS OUT HER HUSBAND
HAS A BIT OF A WANDERING EYE.

42:10.341 --> 42:11.740
REALLY?

42:11.843 --> 42:12.975
YEAH.

42:13.077 --> 42:14.343
HEY, YOU KNOW, IT'S BETTER
TO FIND OUT THESE THINGS

42:14.445 --> 42:15.344
SOONER THAN LATER.

42:15.446 --> 42:16.712
THAT WAY, WE CAN ASK
FOR AN ANNULMENT.

42:16.814 --> 42:19.148
IF NOT, WE GO TO BATTLE...

42:19.250 --> 42:21.683
WHICH IS EXACTLY WHY WE NEED
TO GET ON TOP OF THIS.

42:22.887 --> 42:24.353
[SIGHS]

42:24.455 --> 42:26.021
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

42:26.123 --> 42:27.890
IT'S JUST...

42:27.992 --> 42:30.826
WELL, COLLIN AND SOPHIA SEEM
REALLY HAPPY, DON'T THEY?

42:30.928 --> 42:33.462
YEAH, ABOUT AS HAPPY
AS THAT WOMAN IN MY OFFICE WAS

42:33.564 --> 42:34.730
EARLIER ON HER WEDDING DAY.

42:34.832 --> 42:36.665
PEOPLE IN UNHAPPY

42:36.767 --> 42:38.400
RELATIONSHIPS AND MARRIAGES

42:38.502 --> 42:40.102
SHOULD JUST... MOVE ON.

42:41.906 --> 42:43.405
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT. OKAY.

42:43.507 --> 42:44.974
SO WHAT DO WE DO?

42:45.076 --> 42:47.076
I DON'T KNOW.
SOPHIA'S NOT TALKING TO ME.

42:47.178 --> 42:48.911
DO YOU BLAME HER?

42:49.013 --> 42:50.980
COLLIN...
I DON'T EVEN RECOGNIZE COLLIN.

42:51.082 --> 42:52.047
WHEN HE WAS WITH EMILY,
HE WAS...

42:52.149 --> 42:53.949
HE WAS STEADY,
HE WAS ON THE RIGHT PATH,

42:54.051 --> 42:55.517
HE WAS...

42:55.619 --> 42:56.585
WHOA... EMILY?

42:56.687 --> 42:57.619
WHO'S EMILY?

42:57.721 --> 42:58.787
HIS EX-GIRLFRIEND.

43:00.591 --> 43:01.456
HOW LONG AGO?

43:02.860 --> 43:04.059
WHAT DOES IT MATTER?

43:04.161 --> 43:08.898
NO, BECAUSE IF WE CAN GET
COLLIN AND EMILY TOGETHER...

43:09.000 --> 43:10.366
NO.

43:10.467 --> 43:13.369
NO, NO, NO. I DO NOT WANT
TO BRING EMILY INTO THIS. NO.

43:13.470 --> 43:14.770
WENDY, THIS MAY BE
OUR ONLY HOPE.

43:14.872 --> 43:18.173
SOPHIA, THIS WEEKEND, IS GOING
TO GO TO HER MOTHER'S.

43:18.276 --> 43:20.276
LET'S PUT THEM TOGETHER
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

43:21.345 --> 43:23.545
MARCO... I DON'T...
I DON'T KNOW. THAT'S...

43:24.982 --> 43:26.015
WENDY...

43:26.117 --> 43:29.218
WE DON'T WANT OUR CHILDREN
TO GET HURT HERE.

43:29.320 --> 43:30.319
WE'RE IN THIS TOGETHER.

43:31.822 --> 43:32.955
[DOOR OPENS]

43:33.057 --> 43:34.790
YOO-HOO!
MARCO!

43:34.892 --> 43:35.925
THERE YOU ARE,
MY DANCE PARTNER.

43:36.027 --> 43:36.926
HI...

43:37.028 --> 43:39.028
I HAVE BEEN LOOKING
EVERYWHERE FOR YOU.

43:39.130 --> 43:41.130
NOW, I NEED TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT
THE DANCE CLASSES AT THE HALL.

43:41.232 --> 43:42.231
BEVERLY, I...

43:42.333 --> 43:44.333
I HAVE BEEN PENCILING
YOU IN FOR TONIGHT,

43:44.435 --> 43:46.101
AND THEN NEXT FRIDAY
AND SUNDAY...

43:46.203 --> 43:47.369
BEVERLY, CAN WE JUST TALK
ABOUT THIS LATER, PLEASE?

43:47.471 --> 43:48.170
NO, YOU KNOW WHAT?
THAT'S...

43:48.272 --> 43:49.204
NO, NO, NO...

43:49.307 --> 43:51.040
YOU WORK IT OUT WITH
YOUR DANCE PARTNER.

43:51.142 --> 43:53.342
I HAVE TO GET GOING.

43:54.445 --> 43:55.844
DO YOU KNOW THE TANGO?

44:05.456 --> 44:06.588
TA-DAH!

44:06.690 --> 44:08.424
SO, IN HONOR
OF NATIONAL BIOLOGY WEEK,

44:08.525 --> 44:12.361
WE HAVE A RIVETING DRAMA
ABOUT LIFE IN THE TAIGA.

44:12.463 --> 44:13.728
TAIGA?

44:13.831 --> 44:14.796
OH, YEAH.

44:14.898 --> 44:16.098
IT'S THE WORLD'S LARGEST
TERRESTRIAL BIOMES

44:16.200 --> 44:18.100
OF CONIFEROUS FORESTS,
PINES, SPRUCES, LARCHES...

44:18.202 --> 44:19.835
LET'S GO DANCING.

44:21.038 --> 44:21.937
DANCING?

44:22.039 --> 44:22.904
OH, NO, BUT IT'S DVD NIGHT.

44:23.007 --> 44:24.106
COME ON. IT'LL BE FUN.

44:24.208 --> 44:26.408
BUT... THE TAIGA...

44:37.989 --> 44:41.123
YOU KNOW, WENDY...
IT'S BEEN SOME TIME...

44:41.225 --> 44:43.092
ACTUALLY, A REALLY LONG TIME
SINCE I'VE DANCED,

44:43.194 --> 44:46.395
AND EVEN THEN, IN COTILLION,

44:46.497 --> 44:48.830
YOU KNOW, I HAVE TO SAY,
I NEVER REALLY MASTERED...

44:48.932 --> 44:50.165
COME ON, LOGAN,
IT WON'T BE THAT BAD.

44:50.267 --> 44:52.201
RIGHT, BUT IF I HAD KNOWN
YOU'D WANTED TO GO DANCING,

44:52.303 --> 44:53.535
I COULD'VE PRACTICED A LITTLE.

44:53.637 --> 44:56.071
I'M SURE THERE ARE SOME
VERY GOOD INSTRUCTIONAL VIDEOS

44:56.173 --> 44:58.240
ON THE RHYTHMIC PATTERN
OF THE WALTZ AND, UH...

44:58.342 --> 44:59.774
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE
A LOT OF FUN.

44:59.877 --> 45:00.942
COME ON.

45:08.019 --> 45:09.385
ARE YOU SURE YOU WOULDN'T WANT
TO TRY BOWLING INSTEAD?

45:09.487 --> 45:10.419
BOWLING IS...

45:10.521 --> 45:11.586
DON'T WORRY.

45:11.688 --> 45:14.256
I'M SURE WE'LL AMAZE
THEM WITH OUR MOVES.

45:14.358 --> 45:16.525
♪ HERE COMES LOVE

45:16.627 --> 45:19.661
♪ AND ALL OF THE JOY IT BRINGS

45:19.763 --> 45:23.165
♪ AND ALL OF THOSE
CRAZY THINGS I DO ♪

45:23.267 --> 45:25.700
♪ FOR FALLING IN LOVE
WITH YOU ♪

45:34.878 --> 45:36.245
HI. NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN!

45:36.347 --> 45:37.546
I'M BEVERLY.

45:37.648 --> 45:39.781
HAVE YOU BOTH COME
TO SIGN UP AS DANCE PARTNERS?

45:41.118 --> 45:42.217
UH, I'M...

45:42.319 --> 45:44.319
I'M WENDY,
AND THIS IS LOGAN,

45:44.422 --> 45:45.987
MY, UM...

45:46.090 --> 45:47.889
BOYFRIEND.

45:47.991 --> 45:49.925
HI, BEVERLY.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

45:50.027 --> 45:51.560
IS THIS A DANCE CLASS?

45:51.662 --> 45:53.728
YES, IT IS A DANCE CLASS...
FOR THE RETIREMENT RESIDENTS.

45:53.830 --> 45:55.897
WE'VE BEEN DOING IT FOR
YEARS. THEY JUST LOVE IT.

45:55.999 --> 45:58.333
ESPECIALLY
WHEN THEY GET TO DANCE

45:58.436 --> 45:59.834
WITH SOME OF THE YOUNGER FOLKS,

45:59.937 --> 46:00.969
LIKE THAT MR. AMORINI.

46:01.072 --> 46:03.238
[♪♪♪]

46:05.042 --> 46:06.641
THE WOMEN JUST ADORE HIM.

46:08.845 --> 46:10.179
OH, "NATIONAL BIOLOGY WEEK!"

46:10.281 --> 46:12.147
WILL YOU BE ATTENDING?

46:12.249 --> 46:13.848
PERSONALLY,
I WOULDN'T MISS IT.

46:13.951 --> 46:15.016
I HEAR THEY'RE GOING TO SET
A RECORD

46:15.119 --> 46:18.019
FOR THE MOST TREES PLANTED
IN LESS THAN A MINUTE.

46:18.122 --> 46:18.687
YOU DON'T SAY!

46:18.789 --> 46:19.754
SHOULD BE EXCITING.

46:19.856 --> 46:20.822
YEAH!

46:20.924 --> 46:22.357
EXCUSE ME.

46:25.262 --> 46:27.396
LOGAN, THIS WAS
A BAD IDEA.

46:27.498 --> 46:28.397
LET'S LEAVE.

46:30.801 --> 46:32.301
WENDY!

46:33.804 --> 46:34.703
YOU HERE TO DANCE?

46:34.805 --> 46:36.805
YES... YES, WE ARE.

46:36.907 --> 46:37.906
GREAT.

46:39.210 --> 46:41.843
UH... MARCO, LOGAN.
LOGAN, MARCO.

46:41.945 --> 46:45.514
AH, THE DIVORCE ATTORNEY/
FUTURE FATHER-IN-LAW.

46:45.616 --> 46:47.483
WELL, YOU GOT
ONE OF THOSE PEGGED.

46:47.585 --> 46:48.817
AND YOU ARE...?

46:48.919 --> 46:50.519
BOYFRIEND.

46:53.056 --> 46:54.055
AH.

46:55.058 --> 46:56.891
-LOGAN, LET'S DANCE.
-OKAY.

46:56.994 --> 46:57.859
[BEVERLY]:
MARCO, MARCO...

46:57.961 --> 46:59.361
YES?

46:59.463 --> 47:00.695
YOUR NEXT DANCE PARTNER
IS WAITING.

47:00.797 --> 47:01.597
OH, OF COURSE.

47:01.698 --> 47:04.299
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU,
LOGAN...

47:04.401 --> 47:05.400
WENDY...

47:12.643 --> 47:14.576
ONE, TWO,
THREE, FOUR...

47:14.678 --> 47:15.244
[GRUNT IN PAIN]

47:15.346 --> 47:16.945
SORRY. I'M RUSTY.

47:17.047 --> 47:19.814
IT'S OKAY. NO,
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

47:31.728 --> 47:33.328
YOU KNOW, WENDY,
I'VE BEEN THINKING.

47:33.430 --> 47:34.929
UM, YOU AND I HAVE BEEN DATING
FOR A WHILE NOW...

47:35.032 --> 47:36.931
AND TO ME, IT JUST
MAKES PERFECT SENSE

47:37.034 --> 47:39.801
THAT WE SHOULD
TAKE THIS... THIS "US"...

47:39.903 --> 47:40.869
YOU KNOW, TO THE NEXT LEVEL.

47:40.971 --> 47:42.771
AND, YOU KNOW, I JUST... OH!

47:42.873 --> 47:44.173
ARE YOU OKAY?

47:44.275 --> 47:45.940
I'M GOOD.
IT'S ALL RIGHT. REALLY.

47:46.043 --> 47:47.176
YEAH. NO, IT'S FINE.

47:47.278 --> 47:48.877
-I REALLY GOTCHA THERE.
-NO, IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.

47:48.979 --> 47:49.878
[MUSIC FINISHES WITH FLOURISH]

47:49.980 --> 47:50.979
OH...

47:51.081 --> 47:52.447
UH, LOGAN...

47:53.717 --> 47:55.250
WOULD YOU GET ME
SOMETHING TO DRINK?

47:55.352 --> 47:57.319
SURE.

47:57.421 --> 47:58.387
OKAY.

48:06.830 --> 48:07.896
[ROMANTIC JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS]

48:13.337 --> 48:15.571
<i>POSSO AVERE</i>
<i>QUESTO BALLO?</i>

48:17.107 --> 48:18.873
YOU KNOW I CAN'T SPEAK ITALIAN.

48:18.975 --> 48:20.709
AH...

48:20.811 --> 48:22.311
IT'S THE LANGUAGE
OF LOVE.

48:24.147 --> 48:26.348
IT MEANS,
"MAY I HAVE THIS DANCE?"

48:26.450 --> 48:30.519
♪ A DAY WITHOUT YOU
IS A DAY WITHOUT SUNSHINE ♪

48:30.621 --> 48:34.989
♪ A NIGHT WITHOUT YOU
JUST A LITTLE BIT BLUE ♪

48:35.092 --> 48:38.760
♪ YOU LIGHT UP MY LIFE
LIKE THE SUN IN THE SKY ♪

48:38.862 --> 48:41.563
♪ HEAVEN KNOWS WHY
I FEEL LIKE I DO ♪

48:41.665 --> 48:45.367
♪ IT MAY BE YOUR EYES
MAY BE YOUR KISSES ♪

48:45.469 --> 48:46.501
YOU KNOW...

48:46.604 --> 48:48.704
UM... WHEN YOU MENTIONED
THE THING ABOUT EMILY

48:48.805 --> 48:49.705
THE OTHER DAY,

48:49.806 --> 48:51.506
I DON'T KNOW
THAT I FEEL COMFORTABLE...

48:51.609 --> 48:53.475
SHH.

48:53.577 --> 48:54.809
JUST DANCE.

48:54.911 --> 48:58.280
♪ SOMETHING IS MISSING
WHEN YOU'RE NOT WITH ME ♪

48:58.382 --> 49:03.084
♪ HEAVEN KNOWS WHY
I FEEL LIKE I DO ♪

49:03.186 --> 49:07.489
♪ BUT HEAVEN KNOWS I'M CRAZY
I'M CRAZY ABOUT YOU ♪

49:07.591 --> 49:09.858
♪ HEAVEN KNOWS
I'M CRAZY ABOUT YOU ♪

49:11.262 --> 49:12.628
♪ WALKING DOWN THE AVENUE

49:15.466 --> 49:16.831
♪ DREAMING

49:17.834 --> 49:20.669
♪ WISHING I COULD BE WITH YOU

